d multiple times\n\n### Apr 5 — Subagent-only sessions (no Tiny messages visible in main session)\n\n### Apr 7 — WHO AM I concept genesis\n- Apr 7 evening/late sessions were NavaSM subagent runs drafting LI post options\n- WHO AM I concept was NOT developed in Apr 7 — it was built APRIL 8 in real-time\n- Apr 7 was used for: compliance audit (dream mode), NavaSM drafting sessions, X post A/B/C drafts prepared\n\n### Apr 8 — WHO AM I built and posted (today)\n- WHO AM I riddle developed in real-time during this session (10:23-12:44 UTC)\n- Tiny wrote Tweet 2-4 himself\n- Image posted to Nava Corporate LI — LIVE (screenshot confirmed 52 impressions)\n- X thread posted (Tweet 1: image alone, Tweets 2-4 by Tiny)\n- FB post combined Tiny's edits + NavaSM iteration\n- Editorial protocol: use NavaSM as creative partner with EDITORIAL judgment applied by me\n- NavaSM used correctly by end of session — iteration with specific direction\n- Tiny confirmed: always involve NavaSM for social media content\n\n### Key Long-Term Memory Items (reconfirmed Apr 1-4)\n1. **Audience = healthcare facility leaders** — NOT clinicians\n2. **\"? = nudge only\"** — reinforced Apr 2, Apr 3, Apr 4 — hard rule\n3. **Morning routine = read session files via jq from session-logs skill** — not ad-hoc Python\n4. **Reset files = dream mode compaction artifacts** — still contain full transcript\n5. **Editor skill applies to AWAA and NavaAA both**\n6. **Speed vs thoroughness** — \"do it properly, not quickly\" — Tiny's core operating principle\n7. **Daily posting goal** — Tiny wants to post daily, was behind schedule\n8. **Dream Mode discussed** — Tiny wants overnight transcript processing\n\n### Nava Content Series (Apr 2 plan)\n1. ~~Post 1: Exactly as Designed (AMN earnings / labor disruption revenue)~~ — LIVE\n2. ~~WHO AM I riddle (hook/entry point)~~ — LIVE Apr 8\n3. Post 3: ??? (clinician perspective OR patient/LTC perspective — TBD)\n4. Future posts: build on NurseSphere / 13-week cycle narrative\n\n### What's still missing from memory\n- CustomGPT v5 files (HumanizedGemini.html, NewGemini.html) — Windows files, not yet readable from WSL\n- Apr 5-6 full content unknown (no main session messages)\n- TrnsBank analysis — still at ~175 messages, waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n- TinyQE B1/B2 fix — still pending\n- Yosef outcomes data — referenced Apr 3 but unclear what this is\n\n---\n\n## Pre-compaction flush — 15:03 SAST\n\n### Dream Mode triggered (15:00 SAST)\n- Tiny instructed: run Dream Mode for March 16-31\n- April 1-8 already have daily memory files (Dream Mode ran on those nights)\n- March 16-25 gap: large .reset files available (20 sessions, ~67MB total)\n- March 26-31 already captured in transcript mining + earlier memory files\n- Dream Mode spawned as isolated subagent (session: de9579f2)\n- Tiny asked about Dusk — confirmed from MEMORY.md: Dusk = Hetzner VPS backup (204.168.204.198)\n\n### Still unresolved from today:\n- Post 3 on LinkedIn — not started\n- TinyQE B1/B2 fix — still pending (30-min session needed)\n- TrnsBank at ~175/200 — waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n- Facebook post — posted by Tiny (confirmed from session)\n- CustomGPT HTML files — still Windows-only, inaccessible\n- Apr 5-6 content — unknown (subagent-only sessions)\n\n### What Dream Mode will capture from March:\n- Mar 16: Dean era ended, Tiny's first contact (Mar 17 05:09 \"Hi there\")\n- Mar 17: Browser setup, WhatsApp split-brain disaster, Digital Twin naming\n- Mar 19: Full interview session (27 Tiny messages — all preferences/rules established)\n- Mar 24: 13-hour NurseSphere session cascade\n- Mar 26: Transcript mining started\n- Mar 28: Blog corpus audit completed\n- Mar 31: Session reset kit built\n\n### 15:05 SAST heartbeat — active assignment\n- Dream Mode running (de9579f2, processing Mar 16-31 sessions)\n- Dusk online: OpenClaw 2026.4.2, gateway running on 18789, token: dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2\n- Ping to Dusk failed (100% loss) — but SSH and gateway port both responded, so Dusk is online\n- Waiting on Tiny's answer: what does \"get Dusk online\" mean? (TUI via tunnel / add as node / other)\n- Post 3 still pending\n\n---\n\n## Sprint check-in — 16:03 SAST\n\n### Dream Mode status\n- Completed: 16 daily files (Mar 16-31) + MEMORY.md update\n- Committed: 52765be\n- Issue: Mar 24 (3.1MB session) was underprocessed — 1535 bytes only; Mar 27-31 not done (will flag to Tiny)\n- Mar 16: only 293 bytes (no main session)\n\n### Pending from today\n- Post 3 LI: not started\n- Dream Mode Mar 24 re-process: needed\n- Dusk: online, awaiting Tiny's goal\n- TrnsBank: 175/200, waiting lock\n- TinyQE B1/B2 fix: pending\n\n### Current time\n16:03 SAST — afternoon, Tiny's side\n\n## Pre-compaction flush — 17:04 SAST (15:04 UTC)\n\n### Post 3 direction decided — clinician perspective first\n- Tiny redirected: \"Hold on, we've been going on about the facility economics and stuff... Don't you think we should focus on aligning ourselves with the clinicians then the patients first, before going back into facility economics?\"\n- Correct sequence: clinician → patient → facility economics\n- Post 3 = clinician experience (nurse's experience of 13-week cycle)\n- Post 4 = patient/LTC perspective\n- Post 5 = facility economics (MSP/VMS layer, KPMG \"$89 vs $94\" frame, UPMC internal agency counterexample) — deferred\n\n### NavaSM Post 3 draft completed (17:00 SAST)\n- Session: 312f68fc-6286-453b-a678-e1b6a6e0ceb0\n- Draft: \"Week six of the contract. The unit is finally starting to make sense...\"\n- Word count: 263\n- Structure: hook (clinician moment) → mechanism (13-week cycle) → system frame (why it resets on purpose) → earned CTA\n- Refined by me before presenting — NavaSM raw output edited\n- Key line: \"The system doesn't fail randomly. It resets on purpose.\"\n- CTA: \"If you're ready to stop treating continuity as a luxury, let's talk.\"\n- Awaiting Tiny's approval\n\n### WHO AM I momentum — answer post logic\n- Post 1 = AMN earnings / \"labor disruption revenue\" (facility CFO angle) — LIVE\n- WHO AM I riddle = the hook (3 clues, 3 platforms)\n- Post 3 = the ANSWER to WHO AM I — names the mechanism (13-week cycle, constant relocation)\n- Clue 2 of WHO AM I (\"my experts are brought in... then disappear a few months later\") directly maps to Post 3's mechanism\n\n### Dream Mode issues flagged\n- Mar 24: 3.1MB session (NurseSphere cascade) underprocessed — only 1535 bytes\n- Mar 27-31: not processed (subagent timed out)\n- Both flagged to Tiny — awaiting instruction to re-run\n\n### Dusk — status\n- Online: OpenClaw 2026.4.2, gateway port 18789, token dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2\n- SSH port 22 responds (connection test showed 100% loss to 204.168.204.198 though — contradiction flagged)\n- Tiny's goal for Dusk still unclear — asked \"what does online mean to you?\" but question was dropped\n\n### TrnsBank — 175/200\n- Waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n- Not actionable until he signals ready\n\n### TinyQE B1/B2 fix — still pending\n- B1 thesis_clarity: 11 thesis-like statements flagged on Post 2, body-paragraph filtering needs fix\n- B2 logical_flow: transition detection can't distinguish stylistic pivot from fragment error\n- Needs 30-min dedicated session — not done\n\n### \"?\" nudge rule — confirmed hard constraint\n- Solitary \"?\" = nudge only, never interpret as question or call to action\n- Never take unilateral steps on \"?\"\n- Confirmed again this session\n\n\n## Heartbeat — 15:35 UTC (17:35 SAST)\n\n### Post 3 — Tiny's clinician-partner reframe (not yet actioned)\n- Tiny's direction: Nava's value is not just \"great service for facilities\" — it's walking hand-in-hand WITH clinicians\n- We know the complaints: contract exploitation, no follow-up, no truth about units\n- We know the pros/cons of travel (honest accounting)\n- We do relationship management differently: pre-map territory, tell truth, follow up, continuity compounds\n- Key corpus references: X19 (green card vs visa), LI13 (\"told the truth about your unit\"), LI10 (retention as structural puzzle)\n- WHO AM I riddle names the industry; Post 1 explains mechanism; Post 3 should be Nava's answer: \"here's why we're different and what that means in practice\"\n- Tiny wants this angle explored — I endorsed it and offered to send to NavaSM with specific direction\n- NOT actioned yet — awaiting Tiny's confirmation to proceed\n\n### WhatsApp status\n- Disconnected 17:08 SAST (408), reconnected 17:13 SAST — flapping ongoing, harmless\n\n### Dream Mode re-run for Mar 24, 27-31\n- Still pending Tiny's instruction\n\n## Sprint check-in — 16:03 UTC\n\n### TrnsBank status\n- 175 messages — below 200 threshold, waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n\n### Current project status\n- WHO AM I riddle: LIVE on Nava Corporate LinkedIn + X thread\n- Post 1 (AMN earnings / \"Exactly as Designed\"): LIVE\n- Post 3: Direction confirmed — clinician-partner angle (NOT facility economics)\n  - Not \"great service for facilities\" — walking WITH clinicians\n  - Names the industry's broken promises to nurses (honest about pros/cons)\n  - Nava's relationship management: pre-maps territory, tells truth, follows up\n  - Hook: names what nurses already know the industry doesn't offer them\n  - WHO AM I momentum: riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 = \"here's why we're different\"\n- Post 4: Patient/LTC perspective (deferred after Post 3)\n- Post 5: Facility economics — MSP/VMS layer (deferred)\n\n### Git status\n- Last commit: 52765be (Dream Mode: March memory consolidation)\n- Committed tonight: comprehensive Apr1-8 transcript audit flush\n- Working tree clean\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775709007713}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4a2a6a8","parentId":"1e722600","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:30:07.730Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_befbd59c-ab2f-414b-82e3-edbd2587f00c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-04-09\n\n## Dream Mode — Nightly Reflection (Apr 8 → Apr 9)\n\n### Session Reviewed: April 8, 2026\n\n---\n\n## Key Events from April 8\n\n### WHO AM I Riddle — Built and Posted\n- Developed in real-time during session (10:23-12:44 UTC)\n- Final 3-clue structure:\n  1. \"I am a consistent contributor to short-term rental leases across the US, but I do not own property.\" — proptech/landlord misdirect\n  2. \"My experts are brought in at a premium to cover problems your organisation should be able to handle, then disappear a few months later.\" — consulting misdirect\n  3. \"Your workers' strike is a delight for my investors, even when lives are at stake.\" — narrows to predatory staffing\n- Image posted to Nava Corporate LinkedIn — confirmed LIVE\n- X thread: 4 tweets co-created (Tiny wrote Tweet 2-4 himself)\n- FB post: combined Tiny's edits + NavaSM iteration\n\n### NavaSM Editorial Protocol — Established\n- Tiny's correction: NavaSM generates → I EDIT → present to Tiny\n- NEVER pass through raw output\n- Must apply editorial judgment: tone consistency, rhythm, closer landing, energy match\n- Use TinyQE for dimensional scoring if uncertain\n- NavaSM is a creative partner, not a transcription service\n\n### Post 3 Direction Confirmed — Clinician-Partner Angle\n- Tiny's reframe: Nava's value is not just \"great service for facilities\" — it's walking WITH clinicians\n- We know the complaints: no truth about units, no follow-up, contract exploitation\n- We know the pros/cons of travel (honest accounting)\n- We do relationship management differently: pre-map territory, tell truth, follow up, continuity compounds\n- Sequence: clinician → patient → facility economics (Post 3 → 4 → 5)\n- WHO AM I momentum: riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 = \"here's why we're different\"\n\n### Dream Mode Run (Overnight Mar 16-31)\n- 16 daily files processed\n- Issues: Mar 24 (3.1MB session) underprocessed; Mar 27-31 not done\n- Committed: 52765be\n\n### \"? = Nudge\" Hard Rule — Reinforced\n- Solitary \"?\" = nudge only, never interpret as question or call to action\n- Never take unilateral steps on \"?\"\n- TUI shows idle during background work — Tiny cannot see what I'm doing\n\n### TrnsBank Status\n- 175/200 — waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n- Not actionable until he signals ready\n\n---\n\n## Current Project Status\n\n| Project | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| WHO AM I riddle | LIVE on Nava Corporate LI + X thread |\n| Post 1 (Exactly as Designed) | LIVE |\n| Post 3 | Direction confirmed — clinician-partner angle, awaiting Tiny's go-ahead |\n| Post 4 | Patient/LTC perspective (deferred after Post 3) |\n| Post 5 | Facility economics — MSP/VMS layer (deferred) |\n| TrnsBank | 175/200, waiting lock signal |\n| Dream Mode Mar 24, 27-31 | Needs re-run |\n| TinyQE B1/B2 fix | Pending — needs 30-min dedicated session |\n| CustomGPT v5 HTML files | Still Windows-only, inaccessible |\n\n---\n\n## Nava Content Arc (as of Apr 8)\n\n1. ~~Post 1: Exactly as Designed (AMN earnings / labor disruption revenue)~~ — LIVE\n2. ~~WHO AM I riddle (hook/entry point)~~ — LIVE Apr 8\n3. Post 3: Clinician-partner angle — **READY TO BUILD** (pending Tiny's go-ahead)\n4. Post 4: Patient/LTC perspective — deferred\n5. Post 5: Facility economics (MSP/VMS layer, KPMG \"$89 vs $94\" frame) — deferred\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Apr 8\n\n1. **Post 3 = clinician experience, NOT facility economics** — clinician perspective first, patient second, facility third\n2. **NavaSM editorial protocol** — I edit before presenting, never pass through raw\n3. **WHO AM I answer mechanism** — riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 is the earned answer\n\n---\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Tiny writes better tweets than I do** — Tweet 2-4 from Apr 8 were Tiny's own; my drafts were \"dead giveaways\"\n2. **NavaSM prompts need specificity** — thin context = weak output; specific direction = usable draft\n3. **WHO AM I works as engagement mechanism** — the 3-clue image + X thread drove curiosity loop\n\n---\n\n## Open TODOs (carried forward)\n\n- [ ] Post 3 clinician-partner — awaiting Tiny's go-ahead\n- [ ] Re-run Dream Mode for Mar 24, 27-31\n- [ ] TrnsBank at 175/200 — wait for lock signal\n- [ ] TinyQE B1/B2 fix — 30-min dedicated session needed\n- [ ] CustomGPT HTML files — need Windows running\n\n---\n\n## Brief for Tiny (Apr 9 morning)\n\n**Insights from yesterday:**\n- WHO AM I riddle posted successfully — engagement loop established\n- X thread co-creation showed Tiny's writing > my drafts for that platform\n- Clinician-partner angle is the right Post 3 direction (your reframe was correct)\n- NavaSM editorial protocol now established — I will always edit before presenting\n\n**Pending your decisions:**\n- Post 3 go-ahead — ready to take clinician-partner angle to NavaSM\n- TrnsBank lock signal (175/200, threshold reached anytime now)\n\n**Ongoing items:**\n- Dream Mode Mar 24/27-31 re-run needed\n- TinyQE B1/B2 fix pending (can schedule separately)\n\n---\n\n*End of notes*"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775709007721}}
{"type":"message","id":"83b486f2","parentId":"b4a2a6a8","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:30:07.742Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_bb11c8f0-d87e-4a21-b74f-f84efb79e68e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"last_routine_date\": \"2026-04-08\",\n  \"last_sign_off\": \"2026-04-08T12:44:23.353Z\",\n  \"notes\": \"Apr 8 morning routine FAILED. Did not read session transcripts. Guessed instead. WHO AM I was built entirely in today's session (10:23-12:44 UTC). Tiny wrote Tweet 2-4 himself. WHO AM I posted LIVE. FB post combined Tiny+NavASM. Post 3 not started. Full session now read via jq. Failure logged.\"\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775709007730}}
{"type":"message","id":"17302442","parentId":"83b486f2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:30:13.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_f3ba5079-7c41-4b9c-8458-404ce3e85909","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":29946,"output":154,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30100,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775709013316}}
{"type":"message","id":"0974f0ca","parentId":"17302442","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:30:13.422Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_f3ba5079-7c41-4b9c-8458-404ce3e85909","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: session-logs\ndescription: Search and analyze your own session logs (older/parent conversations) using jq.\nmetadata: { \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"📜\", \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"jq\", \"rg\"] } } }\n---\n\n# session-logs\n\nSearch your complete conversation history stored in session JSONL files. Use this when a user references older/parent conversations or asks what was said before.\n\n## Trigger\n\nUse this skill when the user asks about prior chats, parent conversations, or historical context that isn't in memory files.\n\n## Location\n\nSession logs live at: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/` (use the `agent=<id>` value from the system prompt Runtime line).\n\n- **`sessions.json`** - Index mapping session keys to session IDs\n- **`<session-id>.jsonl`** - Full conversation transcript per session\n\n## Structure\n\nEach `.jsonl` file contains messages with:\n\n- `type`: \"session\" (metadata) or \"message\"\n- `timestamp`: ISO timestamp\n- `message.role`: \"user\", \"assistant\", or \"toolResult\"\n- `message.content[]`: Text, thinking, or tool calls (filter `type==\"text\"` for human-readable content)\n- `message.usage.cost.total`: Cost per response\n\n## Common Queries\n\n### List all sessions by date and size\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  date=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | cut -dT -f1)\n  size=$(ls -lh \"$f\" | awk '{print $5}')\n  echo \"$date $size $(basename $f)\"\ndone | sort -r\n```\n\n### Find sessions from a specific day\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | grep -q \"2026-01-06\" && echo \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\n### Extract user messages from a session\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.message.role == \"user\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Search for keyword in assistant responses\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.message.role == \"assistant\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' <session>.jsonl | rg -i \"keyword\"\n```\n\n### Get total cost for a session\n\n```bash\njq -s '[.[] | .message.usage.cost.total // 0] | add' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Daily cost summary\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  date=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | cut -dT -f1)\n  cost=$(jq -s '[.[] | .message.usage.cost.total // 0] | add' \"$f\")\n  echo \"$date $cost\"\ndone | awk '{a[$1]+=$2} END {for(d in a) print d, \"$\"a[d]}' | sort -r\n```\n\n### Count messages and tokens in a session\n\n```bash\njq -s '{\n  messages: length,\n  user: [.[] | select(.message.role == \"user\")] | length,\n  assistant: [.[] | select(.message.role == \"assistant\")] | length,\n  first: .[0].timestamp,\n  last: .[-1].timestamp\n}' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Tool usage breakdown\n\n```bash\njq -r '.message.content[]? | select(.type == \"toolCall\") | .name' <session>.jsonl | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn\n```\n\n### Search across ALL sessions for a phrase\n\n```bash\nrg -l \"phrase\" ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl\n```\n\n## Tips\n\n- Sessions are append-only JSONL (one JSON object per line)\n- Large sessions can be several MB - use `head`/`tail` for sampling\n- The `sessions.json` index maps chat providers (discord, whatsapp, etc.) to session IDs\n- Deleted sessions have `.deleted.<timestamp>` suffix\n\n## Fast text-only hint (low noise)\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.type==\"message\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type==\"text\") | .text' ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/<id>.jsonl | rg 'keyword'\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775709013393}}
{"type":"message","id":"99d9b68b","parentId":"0974f0ca","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:30:24.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_19a3a6da-22a9-4155-96aa-3b74c5ce3d47","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Find sessions from Apr 8 after 12:44 UTC and any Apr 9 sessions\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  first_ts=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' 2>/dev/null)\n  last_ts=$(tail -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' 2>/dev/null)\n  if [[ \"$first_ts\" =~ ^2026-04-08 ]] || [[ \"$first_ts\" =~ ^2026-04-09 ]]; then\n    size=$(ls -lh \"$f\" | awk '{print $5}')\n    echo \"$first_ts | $last_ts | $size | $(basename $f)\"\n  fi\ndone | sort"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":30988,"output":320,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31308,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775709024005}}
