{"type":"message","id":"baa6b18a","parentId":"bf38bb20","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:27:45.209Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_13a6503f-cd15-41f1-89ea-31dadf17239d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Nava RAG — Production Best Practices Notes\n\nDate: 2026-03-17\n\n## 1) Chunking Strategy\n- Use **semantic-preserving chunks** (target 800-1,200 chars for long-form markdown; overlap 120-220 chars).\n- Keep headings with body text to preserve intent and improve retrieval precision.\n- Avoid splitting tables/list logic mid-chunk.\n- Track chunk quality metrics: average token length, heading coverage, orphan chunk ratio.\n\n## 2) Metadata Design (must-have)\nCurrent schema has: `id,path,source_type,chunk_index,text`.\nFor production add:\n- `title`\n- `url` (if source is web)\n- `published_at` / `last_seen_at`\n- `theme` (cost/compliance/retention/etc.)\n- `audience_primary` (LTC/SNF/CHC/acute/etc.)\n- `offer` (Reclaimix/NurseSphere/general staffing)\n- `evidence_level` (opinion, internal claim, external cited, quantified)\n- `geo_scope`\n\nThis enables better filtering, weighted ranking, and safer generation constraints.\n\n## 3) Retrieval Architecture\nRecommended serving order:\n1. Hybrid retrieval (BM25 + vector)\n2. Lightweight rerank (cross-encoder if available; otherwise heuristic rerank by metadata match)\n3. Context assembly with diversity constraints (avoid 5 chunks from same paragraph)\n\nCurrent implementation:\n- BM25 index: `rag/index/bm25_index.json`\n- Vector index: `rag/index/vector_index.json`\n- Query: `rag/index/query_rag.py --mode hybrid`\n\n## 4) Hallucination Controls\n- Require answer templates with **source-cited bullets** (`path + chunk id`).\n- If evidence confidence < threshold, force: \"insufficient evidence in current corpus\".\n- Add **negative constraints** for known confusion domains (exclude `navacenter.com` wellness framing).\n- Use claim checker pass: every generated claim must map to at least one retrieved chunk.\n\n## 5) Evaluation & QA\nTrack both retrieval and generation metrics:\n- Retrieval: Recall@k, MRR, nDCG on a curated query set\n- Groundedness: % answer sentences with explicit source support\n- Faithfulness: contradiction rate against cited context\n- Coverage: % key themes represented in top-k contexts\n\nStart with a 50-query eval set split by intent:\n- strategic positioning\n- compliance risk\n- cost/ROI\n- retention/turnover\n- service offering differentiation\n\n## 6) Corpus Update Cadence\n- Daily: detect changed/new source files and incremental re-index\n- Weekly: full rebuild + regression eval run\n- Monthly: metadata taxonomy review + stale chunk cleanup\n- Event-driven: immediate re-index on major strategy/SOP doc updates\n\n[20 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775734065202}}
{"type":"message","id":"faa00fb3","parentId":"baa6b18a","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:27:51.040Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d14b4687-21e1-444e-a8f2-5d4811c86ede","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/SYNTHESIS_v1.md","limit":50}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_72df7352-749a-45a9-828b-b479467ae940","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/RAG_OPERATOR_GUIDE.md","limit":50}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":50192,"output":202,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50394,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775734071040}}
{"type":"message","id":"0fb25301","parentId":"faa00fb3","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:27:51.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_d14b4687-21e1-444e-a8f2-5d4811c86ede","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Nava Website Synthesis v1 (Initial 22-article corpus)\n\n## Corpus Scope\n- Source: `navahc.com` (article set extracted from `docs/Nava_Blog_Research_Notes.md`)\n- Count: 22 pages\n- Raw HTML: `rag/raw_html/`\n- Working text: `rag/clean_txt/`\n\n## Core Narrative Arcs\n1. **Cost opacity & hidden spend**\n   - Repeated focus on true staffing cost beyond hourly bill rate.\n2. **Reactive hiring failure**\n   - Messaging pushes from short-term fixes to proactive workforce systems.\n3. **Trust deficit in agency relationships**\n   - Emphasis on credibility, accountability, and measurable performance.\n4. **Compliance & risk burden**\n   - Frequent framing around credentialing, standards, and operational exposure.\n5. **Retention and turnover economics**\n   - Early clinician churn positioned as a compounding financial + quality risk.\n6. **Relational/partnership model positioning**\n   - Nava differentiates on partnership depth vs transactional staffing.\n\n## Positioning Signals (for the Nava \"mind\")\n- Tone: operator-level, consequence-aware, anti-fluff.\n- Audience split:\n  - Facility operators/executives needing staffing outcomes\n  - Clinicians/professionals seeking fit and support\n- Product framing hints:\n  - Workforce systems guidance\n  - Structured staffing models\n  - Branded solution motifs (e.g., NurseSphere, Reclaimix)\n\n## Gaps to Close in v2 Synthesis\n- Strip nav/header/footer boilerplate for cleaner extraction.\n- Add per-article metadata:\n  - URL, inferred audience, pain point, claim type, evidence type, CTA.\n- Build contradiction map against docs in `docs/converted/`.\n\n## Immediate Next Step\nCreate a normalized JSONL knowledge corpus (`rag/corpus.jsonl`) with fields:\n- `id`, `source_type`, `url`, `title`, `audience`, `themes[]`, `content`\nThen index it with doc corpus for full RAG.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775734071062}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d05ae6a","parentId":"0fb25301","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:27:51.072Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_72df7352-749a-45a9-828b-b479467ae940","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Nava RAG Operator Guide (v2)\n\n## What exists now\n- Unified chunk corpus: `rag/index/chunks.jsonl`\n- Retrieval indices:\n  - BM25 lexical: `rag/index/bm25_index.json`\n  - Vector: `rag/index/vector_index.json`\n- Build scripts:\n  - `rag/index/build_chunks.py`\n  - `rag/index/build_bm25.py`\n  - `rag/index/build_vector_index.py`\n- Query script:\n  - `rag/index/query_rag.py`\n\n## Rebuild pipeline\n```bash\npython3 rag/index/build_chunks.py\npython3 rag/index/build_bm25.py\n# Use venv python for transformer embeddings (fastembed)\nrag/.venv/bin/python rag/index/build_vector_index.py\n```\n\n## Query examples\n```bash\n# Hybrid retrieval (recommended)\npython3 rag/index/query_rag.py \"healthcare staffing trust deficits\" -k 5 --mode hybrid\n\n# BM25 only\npython3 rag/index/query_rag.py \"bilingual clinicians\" -k 5 --mode bm25 --source website\n\n# Vector only\npython3 rag/index/query_rag.py \"convert agency staff to permanent team\" -k 5 --mode vector\n\n# Hybrid with custom BM25 weight\npython3 rag/index/query_rag.py \"reactive recruitment fails\" -k 8 --mode hybrid --alpha 0.65\n```\n\n## Current schema\nEach chunk includes:\n- `id`\n- `path`\n- `source_type` (`website` or `docs`)\n- `chunk_index`\n- `text`\n\n## Vector backend behavior\n- Preferred backend: `fastembed` (ONNX transformer; installed in `rag/.venv`).\n- Secondary backend: `ollama_embed` (`nomic-embed-text`) if local Ollama embedding endpoint is responsive.\n- Fallback backend: `fallback_hash_embedding` (stdlib-only signed hash vectors + char n-grams).\n- Why fallback exists: keeps retrieval operational in dependency-constrained environments.\n\n[7 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775734071066}}
{"type":"message","id":"a10a579d","parentId":"5d05ae6a","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:28:05.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Nava RAG — Progress Update (Apr 9)**\n\n**What's built:**\n- 22-article corpus from navahc.com (clean_txt + raw_html)\n- Hybrid retrieval: BM25 + vector indices in `rag/index/`\n- Build scripts, query script, operator guide all in `rag/`\n- Best practices doc covers chunking, metadata schema, hallucination controls, eval metrics\n\n**Key files:**\n- `rag/RAG_OPERATOR_GUIDE.md` — how to rebuild/query\n- `rag/PRODUCTION_RAG_BEST_PRACTICES.md` — architecture notes\n- `rag/SYNTHESIS_v1.md` — 22-article narrative map (cost opacity, trust deficit, compliance risk, retention economics, partnership model)\n- `rag/QUEUE_PACK.md` — content queue system\n\n**Gaps flagged:**\n- Per-article metadata (URL, audience, pain point, evidence type) not yet added\n- Contradiction map vs `docs/converted/` not built\n- Corpus update cadence: daily incremental, weekly full rebuild\n\n**Next steps (when you give the word):**\n- Post 3 clinician-partner → NavaSM with full RAG context\n- v2 synthesis with proper metadata schema\n- Blog corpus audit for non-Tiny bylines (from Mar 24 flag)\n\nAnything specific you want actioned first?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":51156,"output":359,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51515,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775734085585}}
