{"type":"message","id":"d1370537","parentId":"f900bc8d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:41:07.407Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed. Facility leaders reading about what it means to align with clinicians — not clinicians reading it themselves.\n\nSpawning NavaSM now with full context.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_70299076-aff5-49df-93fe-eb8b45683c0b","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are NavaSM — a LinkedIn copywriter with a sharp, observational voice. You write for healthcare facility leaders (DONs, CFOs, healthcare administrators) — but your hook comes from the clinician's lived experience.\n\n## Your task\nDraft LinkedIn Post 3 for Nava Healthcare's corporate LinkedIn page.\n\n## Context\n- Post 1 (AMN earnings / \"Exactly as Designed\") — LIVE\n- WHO AM I riddle (3 clues, image post) — LIVE as image post\n- Post 3 builds on WHO AM I momentum — it's the earned answer post\n\n## CRITICAL AUDIENCE REMINDER\nYou are talking to FACILITY LEADERS. Not clinicians. The post is ABOUT clinicians, but the reader is the healthcare administrator who hires, manages, and budgets around them. They need to understand what-alignment-with-clinicians means for THEIR outcomes.\n\n## The clinician-partner angle (confirmed Apr 8 with Tiny)\n- Nava's value: walking WITH clinicians, not just \"great service for facilities\"\n- We know the complaints nurses face: no truth about units, no follow-up, contract exploitation\n- We know the pros/cons of travel (honest accounting)\n- Nava does relationship management differently: pre-map territory, tell truth, follow up, continuity compounds\n- The hook: name what nurses already know the industry doesn't offer them\n\n## The Wichita oncology hook (from corpus)\n\"Eight patients. One CNA. In a rehab unit, that would be a typical Tuesday, but in an oncology unit? That's a crisis.\"\n\nThis ran on corporate LI on Apr 6. Post 3 should NOT repeat that story but should use the nurse's experience of being in that moment as an entry point.\n\n## The 13-week cycle mechanism\nThe travel nurse cycle: choose travel for flexibility, but constant relocation makes it unsustainable. The same mechanism that creates flexibility (13-week contracts, new facilities) also creates instability. Nurses learn not to put down roots. The system resets on purpose — not randomly.\n\n## Editorial rules\n- Write in flowing prose — NO one-liner paragraphs\n- Bold for narrative pivots only (max 2-3 per post)\n- Bridge sentences between paragraphs — use transition words\n- Concrete before abstract: specific nurse moment → system frame\n- CTA must feel earned, not bolted on\n- \"We\" voice (Nava corporate)\n- 200-300 words\n- Read it aloud before finalizing — if it sounds like LinkedIn boilerplate, rewrite\n\n## Format\nOutput the post in this structure:\n1. Hook (clinician moment — concrete, specific)\n2. The mechanism (what the 13-week cycle actually does to the people inside it)\n3. The system frame (why this keeps happening — the business model)\n4. The earned CTA (Nava's role — what walking with clinicians means for facility leaders)\n\nStart directly with the first sentence — no preamble.\n\n## The WHO AM I bridge\nRemember: Clue 2 of WHO AM I was \"My experts are brought in at a premium to cover problems your organisation should be able to handle, then disappear a few months later.\" Post 3 is the answer to that riddle — it explains WHY they disappear and what the system has to gain from it.","runtime":"subagent","mode":"run"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":61238,"output":1430,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62668,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775734867403}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb579513","parentId":"d1370537","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:41:08.351Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_70299076-aff5-49df-93fe-eb8b45683c0b","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:dac0c71a-92ee-466c-bc9b-6b8f2683239a\",\n  \"runId\": \"51f4968d-f05f-4ce5-9cc4-82d879416a3f\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:dac0c71a-92ee-466c-bc9b-6b8f2683239a","runId":"51f4968d-f05f-4ce5-9cc4-82d879416a3f","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775734868334}}
