{"type":"message","id":"fa236545","parentId":"eabc19ea","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:58:55.081Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_ec0948a1-3de3-4a7e-9f0f-fe8c593b30bf","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"usage: tinyqe.py [-h] [--format {json,narrative}]\n                 [--dimensions DIMENSIONS [DIMENSIONS ...]]\n                 [text]\n\nTinyQE: Tiny Quality Evaluator\n\npositional arguments:\n  text                  Text to evaluate. If not provided, reads from stdin.\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --format {json,narrative}\n                        Output format\n  --dimensions DIMENSIONS [DIMENSIONS ...]\n                        Specific dimensions to run (e.g., A1 A2 B1). Default:\n                        all available."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":188,"aggregated":"usage: tinyqe.py [-h] [--format {json,narrative}]\n                 [--dimensions DIMENSIONS [DIMENSIONS ...]]\n                 [text]\n\nTinyQE: Tiny Quality Evaluator\n\npositional arguments:\n  text                  Text to evaluate. If not provided, reads from stdin.\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --format {json,narrative}\n                        Output format\n  --dimensions DIMENSIONS [DIMENSIONS ...]\n                        Specific dimensions to run (e.g., A1 A2 B1). Default:\n                        all available.","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775735935064}}
{"type":"message","id":"d43af1a8","parentId":"fa236545","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:59:02.803Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_978ee10f-7ea5-42be-bddd-d4c41bdff265","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && python3 tinyqe/tinyqe.py --format narrative << 'TINYQE_EOF'\nA nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally stops second-guessing where the supplies are kept. Week nine, and she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows. She's learning the room. She could stay.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, her contract ends, and the unit loses her before the investment matures.\n\n**Here's what most facilities don't see clearly: the 13-week contract was designed this way.** The same mechanism that gives nurses geographic flexibility also resets them — deliberately — before continuity can form. A traveler who starts to know your unit intimately is a traveler who's harder to place next. So the system moves them before that happens. The architecture of travel staffing doesn't optimize for stability. It optimizes for throughput.\n\nWhich means the \"premium\" isn't just a rate card line item. You're paying for someone to navigate a learning curve that was never meant to resolve. The contract ends before the investment pays off. Your unit absorbs the turnover cost — the orientation gaps, the hand-off errors, the nurses who leave because the deal was structured to end.\n\n**The nurses see it coming.** Some negotiate to come back. Some choose to stay. But many leave because the business model requires it — not because the clinician chose to exit.\n\nWe built Nava differently. We believe continuity requires someone who stays. So we structure around that — telling truth up front, following up after arrival, building relationships that outlast a contract cycle.\n\nIf you'd like to hear more about what that looks like in practice, let's talk.\nTINYQE_EOF"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":66433,"output":379,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66812,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775735942801}}
{"type":"message","id":"00fa7760","parentId":"d43af1a8","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:59:03.155Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_978ee10f-7ea5-42be-bddd-d4c41bdff265","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TinyQE Assessment — Linkedin\n\nOverall: Actionable. Content has strengths but needs refinement in key areas.\n\nTop 3 Priorities:\n1. Thesis Clarity (severity: medium | weight: 15%) — Multiple thesis-like statements detected (9). This may be acceptable for narrative posts.\n   → In short-form: the opening line is hook+thesis. Body paragraphs should develop it, not introduce new claims. Merge or cut secondary claims.\n2. Argumentative Rigor (severity: medium | weight: 8%) — Multiple fallacies detected: begging_the_question. Argument logic is compromised.\n   → Major revision needed: eliminate fallacies, ensure claims are supported by evidence, and use clear logical connectors.\n3. Evidence Quality (severity: medium | weight: 12%) — Some claims supported by logical evidence, but coverage may be uneven.\n   → Ensure all major claims have corresponding evidence. Consider strengthening weak evidence.\n\nNote: Scores are diagnostic, not judgmental. Focus on the priority queue for actionable feedback.\nFormat detected: Linkedin (confidence: 70%)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":322,"aggregated":"TinyQE Assessment — Linkedin\n\nOverall: Actionable. Content has strengths but needs refinement in key areas.\n\nTop 3 Priorities:\n1. Thesis Clarity (severity: medium | weight: 15%) — Multiple thesis-like statements detected (9). This may be acceptable for narrative posts.\n   → In short-form: the opening line is hook+thesis. Body paragraphs should develop it, not introduce new claims. Merge or cut secondary claims.\n2. Argumentative Rigor (severity: medium | weight: 8%) — Multiple fallacies detected: begging_the_question. Argument logic is compromised.\n   → Major revision needed: eliminate fallacies, ensure claims are supported by evidence, and use clear logical connectors.\n3. Evidence Quality (severity: medium | weight: 12%) — Some claims supported by logical evidence, but coverage may be uneven.\n   → Ensure all major claims have corresponding evidence. Consider strengthening weak evidence.\n\nNote: Scores are diagnostic, not judgmental. Focus on the priority queue for actionable feedback.\nFormat detected: Linkedin (confidence: 70%)","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775735943145}}
{"type":"message","id":"45c5d0e9","parentId":"00fa7760","timestamp":"2026-04-09T11:59:27.283Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**TinyQE says:**\n\n1. **Thesis clarity** — 9 thesis-like statements. Opening line is hook+thesis, body paragraphs should *develop* it, not introduce new claims. The \"13 weeks was designed this way\" pivot is one too many structural reveals for short-form.\n2. **Argumentative rigor** — \"begging the question\" fallacy. The throughput claim is stated as fact when it needs supporting logic. The argument structure needs tightening.\n3. **Evidence quality** — uneven. Key claims need grounding.\n\n**My read:** The flow is right but the logic has gaps. The \"designed this way\" line asserts motive without establishing mechanism first. Need to sequence: *what happens* → *why it keeps happening* → *the business model explanation*. Right now it's landing the \"designed\" punch before the reader is primed to accept it.\n\n---\n\n**On the website question:**\n\nContact form *is* a shortcut — but it's the right one for now. You're not selling NurseSphere or Reclaimix here, you're establishing Nava's operating philosophy. There's no dedicated \"continuity\" landing page yet.\n\nOption: a brief \"learn more about workforce solutions\" link that goes to navahc.com or a generic contact ask. Not ideal, but honest.\n\nBetter long-term play: when Reclaimix launches properly, this post becomes the bridge to it (your angle above — the DON/ADON sigh of relief, the nurse who chose to come back). That's the next content arc, not this post.\n\nFor now: contact form is fine. This post earns the ask; the destination can be simple.\n\nWant me to fix the logical structure and republish, or are you happy to go with what we have?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":67027,"output":568,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67595,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":