{"type":"message","id":"f7d45bfb","parentId":"97b46c02","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:05:18.335Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-09 14:05 GMT+2] My word, you are on your A-game. I felt off about \"designed this way\" too. This means we made real progress with TinyQE. I think we must assume every reader of our posts is learning about Nava for the first time and they don't know our lore - so they will be like, \"designed this way, wtf are you talking about?\". This is why I did not want TinyQE to have access to our corpus! How do we fix it?\n\nBank the idea about launching Reclaimix properly then linking to it. In the next day or two, even later today, we will create a Reclaimix article."}],"timestamp":1775736318297}}
