{"type":"message","id":"2f14f7cf","parentId":"a75516c8","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:10:08.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_de3bd8eb-ef6a-4196-b93f-bfb1dcb77b51","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat >> /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TrnsBank.md << 'EOF'\n\n## [2026-04-09 14:05 UTC] You:\nMy word, you are on your A-game. I felt off about \"designed this way\" too. This means we made real progress with TinyQE. I think we must assume every reader of our posts is learning about Nava for the first time and they don't know our lore - so they will be like, \"designed this way, wtf are you talking about?\". This is why I did not want TinyQE to have access to our lore! How do we fix it?\n\nBank the idea about launching Reclaimix properly then linking to it. In the next day or two, even later today, we will create a Reclaimix article.\n\n## [2026-04-09 14:09 UTC] Me:\nNotes saved. Two critical lessons:\n1. \"Designed this way\" — conclusion before evidence. Fix: establish mechanism first (weeks 7-9 narrative), THEN name it. Reader follows the logic, then gets the reveal.\n2. TinyQE methodology — never feed corpus context before running evaluation. Run cold, on text alone. The tool should evaluate what the post SAYS, not what the corpus SUPPOSES it means.\n\nAction plan:\n- Post 3 fix: lead with nurse's experience of the cycle, build to the reveal, land the business model frame\n- Reclaimix article: bank idea, create in next 1-2 days\nEOF"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":68737,"output":851,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69588,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775736608542}}
