{"type":"message","id":"9c1bae72","parentId":"bbbdce13","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:10:27.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The \"designed this way\" fix: lead with what the 13-week cycle *does* to a unit, then let the reader reach the conclusion themselves, then name it. Right now we're landing the reveal before the reader has the evidence to follow.\n\nRevised structure:\n\n1. The nurse's experience (weeks 7-9 — learning, finally knowing the room)\n2. Contract ends — she's gone\n3. This isn't random — it happens *every time*\n4. The pattern: the 13-week reset\n5. The business model: why agencies structurally can't want continuity\n6. Nava's answer\n\nReader sees themselves in the pattern before we name it. No lore required.\n\n**On TinyQE:** agreed — lesson learned. From now on it evaluates cold text only. No corpus context, no background. What the post says on its own merits. That's the right methodology.\n\n---\n\nOn Reclaimix: noted. Next 1-2 days. I'll have a Reclaimix article draft ready when you are.\n\nWant me to rewrite Post 3 with the new structure now?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":69101,"output":414,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69515,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775736627459}}
