{"type":"message","id":"f4c3b712","parentId":"f0d6893d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:25:47.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TrnsBank analysis complete. Wiped at cap, committed eb1ff2d.\n\n**7 durable lessons extracted:**\n1. Never replace valuable content — only enhance\n2. Append every turn to TrnsBank — not just when reminded\n3. Update editor skill when Tiny says so\n4. Don't overcorrect to the opposite extreme\n5. No lore assumptions — every post stands alone\n6. TinyQE cold-run only — no corpus context\n7. I vs We voice — corporate vs personal\n\nAlso still waiting on your Post 3 sign-off — ready to publish when you are."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":65551,"output":178,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65729,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775737547242}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7962415","parentId":"f4c3b712","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:26:45.679Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-09 14:26 GMT+2] Not yet. I have one more editorial note. Learning where the supplies are? Maybe some units are hard to navigate but I'm pretty sure I can teach my 7 year-old brother where to find the medicine cabinate in 2 days. Why would it take a trained clinician 7 weeks? How about this: A travelling nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows."}],"timestamp":1775737605659}}
{"type":"message","id":"00c95f6e","parentId":"a7962415","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:27:02.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e55a043c-97ba-40de-a3f1-e26ff20f9d5d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat >> /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TrnsBank.md << 'EOF'\n\n## [2026-04-09 14:26 UTC] You:\nNot yet. I have one more editorial note. Learning where the supplies are? Maybe some units are hard to navigate but I'm pretty sure I can teach my 7 year-old brother where to find the medicine cabinet in 2 days. Why would it take a trained clinician 7 weeks? How about this: A travelling nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n\n## [2026-04-09 14:26 UTC] Me:\nSharp. The original implies the learning curve is physical/logistical — wrong frame, a child could find the medicine cabinet in days. The real learning curve is social: culture, relationships, belonging. Karaoke is the perfect concrete detail because it names belonging without being sentimental. Updating the hook.\nEOF"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":67081,"output":394,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67475,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775737622889}}
{"type":"message","id":"7af879fd","parentId":"00c95f6e","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:27:02.968Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_e55a043c-97ba-40de-a3f1-e26ff20f9d5d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"(no output)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":29,"aggregated":"","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775737622948}}
{"type":"message","id":"8be6687c","parentId":"7af879fd","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:27:14.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sharp. \"Learning where the supplies are\" implies a logistical problem — a child could figure that out in days. The real learning curve is *social*: culture, belonging, the human texture of a unit. Karaoke is the perfect detail because it names what actually takes seven weeks without being sentimental.\n\nUpdated hook:\n\n---\n\nA travelling nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows. She's embedded.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, and she leaves.\n\n**This happens like clockwork — but not because nurses want to leave.** Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because the structure of the travel model requires it — not because the clinician chose to exit.\n\nThe 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume — new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. So the system moves her before that happens.\n\nYour unit pays the price: hand-off errors, orientation costs, the institutional knowledge that never accumulates because it keeps walking out the door.\n\nWe built Nava differently. Continuity requires someone who stays, so we structure around that from day one — truth at placement, follow-up after arrival, relationships that outlast the contract cycle.\n\nIf you're tired of funding the learning curve, let's talk.\n\n---\n\nBetter. That one detail changes everything."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":67334,"output":397,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67731,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775737634634}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e7a846f","parentId":"8be6687c","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:30:59.749Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-09 14:30 GMT+2] This reminds me of my shock when I saw my second-grade teacher at the market. Why was she there, I thought. She is supposed to be at school! But as you grow older, you learn that authority figures are human. Teachers don't stay at school 24/7 just because you arrive there every weekday and they are there; you leave them there when you go home. Same with clinicians and at Nava, we are all about the human side of clinicians, not just the professional profile."}],"timestamp":1775737859694}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ce16012","parentId":"3e7a846f","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:31:16.119Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_9656e4d3-510a-4f2c-b032-00a21b689d7c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat >> /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TrnsBank.md << 'EOF'\n\n## [2026-04-09 14:30 UTC] You:\nThis reminds me of my shock when I saw my second-grade teacher at the market. Why was she there, I thought. She is supposed to be at school! But as you grow older, you learn that authority figures are human. Teachers don't stay at school 24/7 just because you arrive there every weekday and they are there; you leave them there when you go home. Same with clinicians and at Nava, we are all about the human side of clinicians, not just the professional profile.\n\n## [2026-04-09 14:30 UTC] Me:\nSaved. The teacher-at-the-market moment is a perfect parallel — embeddedness is social, not just professional. The nurse belongs to a community, not just a unit. Nava's differentiator: human side of clinicians, not just the professional profile. This deepens the closer significantly.\nEOF"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":67816,"output":408,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68224,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775737876116}}
