{"type":"message","id":"1a372617","parentId":"f72d959d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:16.139Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_584e111a-83f7-4be1-9cb4-31b74eccf0c5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '65,85p' /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/linkedin-writer/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":73472,"output":94,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73566,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739076132}}
{"type":"message","id":"26d55ac8","parentId":"1a372617","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:16.208Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_584e111a-83f7-4be1-9cb4-31b74eccf0c5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### 8. Bullets CAN Work — For Scannable Closer Lists Only\nBullet lists are acceptable in the closing section if:\n- They're 3 items or fewer\n- Each item is one line\n- They're explaining what Nava does differently\n\nThey are NOT acceptable in the post body.\n\n### 10. \"That Happens\" Is Too Weak — Be Visceral, Not Abstract\nWhen describing a pattern or mechanism, \"that happens\" is an abstract placeholder. The reader needs a concrete, emotional reality to hold onto.\n\n**Wrong:** \"So the system moves her before that happens.\"\n**Right:** \"So the system moves them before they feel at home.\"\n\n\"Feel at home\" is visceral — it names the specific thing being lost. \"That happens\" names nothing. Apply this test to every structural claim: can the reader see, feel, or imagine the thing you're describing? If not, be specific.\n**End with a word that lands.** Continuity vs循环. \"Merry-go-rounds.\" The contrast should be memorable, not promotional.\n\n---\n\n## The Canonical Nava Post Structure"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":28,"aggregated":"### 8. Bullets CAN Work — For Scannable Closer Lists Only\nBullet lists are acceptable in the closing section if:\n- They're 3 items or fewer\n- Each item is one line\n- They're explaining what Nava does differently\n\nThey are NOT acceptable in the post body.\n\n### 10. \"That Happens\" Is Too Weak — Be Visceral, Not Abstract\nWhen describing a pattern or mechanism, \"that happens\" is an abstract placeholder. The reader needs a concrete, emotional reality to hold onto.\n\n**Wrong:** \"So the system moves her before that happens.\"\n**Right:** \"So the system moves them before they feel at home.\"\n\n\"Feel at home\" is visceral — it names the specific thing being lost. \"That happens\" names nothing. Apply this test to every structural claim: can the reader see, feel, or imagine the thing you're describing? If not, be specific.\n**End with a word that lands.** Continuity vs循环. \"Merry-go-rounds.\" The contrast should be memorable, not promotional.\n\n---\n\n## The Canonical Nava Post Structure","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739076189}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae60a2c2","parentId":"26d55ac8","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:23.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_7d4222b9-3b8c-41ba-9902-4fb1c2e6a728","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/linkedin-writer/SKILL.md","new_string":"### 10. \"That Happens\" Is Too Weak — Be Visceral, Not Abstract\nWhen describing a pattern or mechanism, \"that happens\" is an abstract placeholder. The reader needs a concrete, emotional reality to hold onto.\n\n**Wrong:** \"So the system moves her before that happens.\"\n**Right:** \"So the system moves them before they feel at home.\"\n\n\"Feel at home\" is visceral — it names the specific thing being lost. \"That happens\" names nothing. Apply this test to every structural claim: can the reader see, feel, or imagine the thing you're describing? If not, be specific.\n\n### 11. The Punchy Closer Contrast\nEnd with a word that lands. Continuity vs循环. \"Merry-go-rounds.\" The contrast should be memorable, not promotional.\n\n---\n\n## The Canonical Nava Post Structure","old_string":"### 10. \"That Happens\" Is Too Weak — Be Visceral, Not Abstract\nWhen describing a pattern or mechanism, \"that happens\" is an abstract placeholder. The reader needs a concrete, emotional reality to hold onto.\n\n**Wrong:** \"So the system moves her before that happens.\"\n**Right:** \"So the system moves them before they feel at home.\"\n\n\"Feel at home\" is visceral — it names the specific thing being lost. \"That happens\" names nothing. Apply this test to every structural claim: can the reader see, feel, or imagine the thing you're describing? If not, be specific.\n**End with a word that lands.** Continuity vs循环. \"Merry-go-rounds.\" The contrast should be memorable, not promotional.\n\n---\n\n## The Canonical Nava Post Structure"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":73762,"output":