{"type":"message","id":"9e70f2c2","parentId":"9b88f120","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:44.729Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_12eda85c-ef72-4dd4-9209-f2b124cc2179","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && git add -A && git commit -m \"LinkedIn Writer skill: added rule 10 ('that happens' is too weak) and rule 11 (punchy closer). Now 11 editorial rules total.\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":73419,"output":115,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73534,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739104726}}
{"type":"message","id":"02a58410","parentId":"9e70f2c2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:45.040Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_12eda85c-ef72-4dd4-9209-f2b124cc2179","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master a75b5b9] LinkedIn Writer skill: added rule 10 ('that happens' is too weak) and rule 11 (punchy closer). Now 11 editorial rules total.\n 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":254,"aggregated":"[master a75b5b9] LinkedIn Writer skill: added rule 10 ('that happens' is too weak) and rule 11 (punchy closer). Now 11 editorial rules total.\n 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739105019}}
{"type":"message","id":"8afdae8d","parentId":"02a58410","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:57.599Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Skill updated and committed (a75b5b9). Two more rules added: #10 \"that happens\" is too weak, #11 punchy closer contrast.\n\nAlso updating the saved draft with your final changes:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_b3cd2c6a-3331-4917-9605-ecc82f933eed","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# LinkedIn Post 3 — Nava Healthcare Corporate\n**Date:** April 9, 2026\n**Status:** READY TO PUBLISH\n**Topic:** Continuity / Merry-Go-Rounds\n\n---\n\nA travelling nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, and she leaves.\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝗰𝗸𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸, but not because nurses want to leave. Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry.\n\nThe 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume: new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. Familiarity breeds comfort, and places unknown come with uncertainty and social anxiety. So the system moves them before they feel at home.\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘂𝗻𝗶𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘆𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲: hand-off errors, orientation costs, the institutional knowledge that never accumulates because it keeps walking out the door.\n\nWe built Nava differently. Continuity requires someone who stays, so we structure around that from day one:\n • Truth at placement,\n • Follow-up after arrival,\n • Relationships that outlast the contract cycle.\n\n𝗕𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝘄𝗲 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗶𝗻 𝟭𝟯-𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗺𝗲𝗿𝗿𝘆-𝗴𝗼-𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝘀.\n\nIf you're tired of funding the learning curve, let's talk.\n","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/li-post3-2026-04-09.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":73570,"output":592,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739117594}}
{"type":"message","id":"069125dc","parentId":"8afdae8d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:51:57.705Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b3cd2c6a-3331-4917-9605-ecc82f933eed","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 1530 bytes to /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/li-post3-2026-04-09.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739117681}}
{"type":"message","id":"72f48522","parentId":"069125dc","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:52:17.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_5fa9bff5-7111-407d-a239-46fb365c57b4","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# LinkedIn Posts — Nava Healthcare Corporate\n\n## Post 3 — Apr 9, 2026 — Continuity / Merry-Go-Rounds\n\nA travelling nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, and she leaves.\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝗰𝗸𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸, but not because nurses want to leave. Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry.\n\nThe 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume: new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. Familiarity breeds comfort, and places unknown come with uncertainty and social anxiety. So the system moves them before they feel at home.\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘂𝗻𝗶𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘆𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲: hand-off errors, orientation costs, the institutional knowledge that never accumulates because it keeps walking out the door.\n\nWe built Nava differently. Continuity requires someone who stays, so we structure around that from day one:\n • Truth at placement,\n • Follow-up after arrival,\n • Relationships that outlast the contract cycle.\n\n𝗕𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝘄𝗲 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗶𝗻 𝟭𝟯-𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗺𝗲𝗿𝗿𝘆-𝗴𝗼-𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝘀.\n\nIf you're tired of funding the learning curve, let's talk.\n\n---\n","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":73671,"output":518,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74189,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739137028}}
