{"type":"message","id":"91149af8","parentId":"0e10261b","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:54:41.500Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_c93cd2a0-cc52-4c9a-8773-943d168ccbfa","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md."}],"details":{"diff":"  1 # LinkedIn Posts — Nava Healthcare Corporate\n  2 \n  3 ## Post 3 — Apr 9, 2026 — Continuity / Merry-Go-Rounds\n  4 \n- 5 A travelling nurse reaches week seven of her contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, she's started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n+ 5 A travelling nurse reaches week seven of their contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, they've started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n  6 \n- 7 Then week thirteen arrives, and she leaves.\n+ 7 Then week thirteen arrives, and they leave.\n  8 \n  9 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝗰𝗸𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸, but not because nurses want to leave. Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry.\n 10 \n 11 The 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume: new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. Familiarity breeds comfort, and places unknown come with uncertainty and social anxiety. So the system moves them before they feel at home.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":5},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739281468}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2dff295","parentId":"91149af8","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:54:48.583Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_2618342f-0568-4794-8694-90473179eadf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && git add -A && git commit -m \"Post 3: they/them for nurse - gender neutrality applied throughout. Skill example fixed.\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":62263,"output":77,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62340,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739288580}}
{"type":"message","id":"1fb7861b","parentId":"e2dff295","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:54:48.953Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_2618342f-0568-4794-8694-90473179eadf","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master 4459815] Post 3: they/them for nurse - gender neutrality applied throughout. Skill example fixed.\n 3 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":315,"aggregated":"[master 4459815] Post 3: they/them for nurse - gender neutrality applied throughout. Skill example fixed.\n 3 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775739288928}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9656d85","parentId":"1fb7861b","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:54:58.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nSkill now 12 rules, examples clean, Post 3 gender-neutral throughout.\n\n**Rule 12** added — male nurses are not mythical. \"Doctor = he, nurse = she\" is a stereotype. Use \"they\" when gender is unknown.\n\nFinal Post 3:\n\nA travelling nurse reaches week seven of their contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, they've started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, and they leave.\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝗰𝗸𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸, but not because nurses want to leave. Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry.\n\nThe 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume: new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. Familiarity breeds comfort, and places unknown come with uncertainty and social anxiety. So the system moves them before they feel at home.\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘂𝗻𝗶𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘆𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲: hand-off errors, orientation costs, the institutional knowledge that never accumulates because it keeps walking out the door.\n\nWe built Nava differently. Continuity requires someone who stays, so we structure around that from day one:\n • Truth at placement,\n • Follow-up after arrival,\n • Relationships that outlast the contract cycle.\n\n𝗕𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝘄𝗲 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗶𝗻 𝟭𝟯-𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗺𝗲𝗿𝗿𝘆-𝗴𝗼-𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝘀.\n\nIf you're tired of funding the learning curve, let's talk.\n\nReady to publish."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":62382,"output":503,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62885,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739298523}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cd22d14","parentId":"d9656d85","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:57:02.636Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-04-09 14:57 GMT+2] Perfect, published. Add it to the corpus. Now we need the X version. Work it out with NavaSM and TinyQE and give me results."}],"timestamp":1775739422599}}
{"type":"message","id":"52421691","parentId":"3cd22d14","timestamp":"2026-04-09T12:57:26.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_7bb4c70c-4cd0-41bb-9f7e-ef73d2f2b8a4","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are NavaSM — a sharp social media copywriter for Nava Healthcare.\n\n## Your task\nDraft an X (Twitter) version of Post 3 — the continuity/merry-go-round post that just went live on LinkedIn.\n\n## The LinkedIn post (for reference):\nA travelling nurse reaches week seven of their contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, they've started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, and they leave.\n\nThis happens like clockwork, but not because nurses want to leave. Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry.\n\nThe 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume: new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. Familiarity breeds comfort, and places unknown come with uncertainty and social anxiety. So the system moves them before they feel at home.\n\nYour unit pays the price: hand-off errors, orientation costs, the institutional knowledge that never accumulates because it keeps walking out the door.\n\nWe built Nava differently. Continuity requires someone who stays, so we structure around that from day one:\n • Truth at placement,\n • Follow-up after arrival,\n • Relationships that outlast the contract cycle.\n\nBecause we don't deal in 13-week merry-go-rounds.\n\nIf you're tired of funding the learning curve, let's talk.\n\n## Context\n- WHO AM I riddle (Clue 2): \"My experts are brought in at a premium to cover problems your organisation should be able to handle, then disappear a few months later.\"\n- Post 3 is the answer to that riddle — it explains WHY they disappear\n- X format: 280 chars per tweet, can thread up to 3-4 tweets\n- X readers don't know Nava — stand alone\n- Thread header: no emoji signals — design it to make readers want to keep reading\n\n## X-specific rules\n- Single tweets: compressed, punchy, no fluff\n- Thread: each tweet is a chapter, not a standalone\n- First tweet: scroll-stopper + navigation cue\n- Contrast creates discovery — open with what readers think they understand, reveal what they don't\n- Final tweet: data + diagnosis + urgency + CTA if earlier tweets built correctly\n- \"Time is ticking\" closer addition — adds urgency without repeating argument structure\n- Bold CAN appear in X threads for emphasis\n\n## Editorial rules\n- Gender neutral (\"they\" for individuals)\n- No lore assumptions — X readers know nothing about Nava\n- No \"structure requires it\" — humanize the mechanism\n- End with a word that lands — merry-go-rounds, learning curve, etc.\n\n## Output\nProvide either:\n1. A single tweet (≤280 chars) — if the full idea fits\n2. A 2-3 tweet thread — if condensation requires it\n\nStart directly with the first sentence — no preamble.</task>\n<parameter name=\"runtime\">subagent","mode":"run"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":74850,"output":885,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75735,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775739446208}}
