st \\\"great service for facilities\\\" — it's walking hand-in-hand WITH clinicians\\n- We know the complaints: contract exploitation, no follow-up, no truth about units\\n- We know the pros/cons of travel (honest accounting)\\n- We do relationship management differently: pre-map territory, tell truth, follow up, continuity compounds\\n- Key corpus references: X19 (green card vs visa), LI13 (\\\"told the truth about your unit\\\"), LI10 (retention as structural puzzle)\\n- WHO AM I riddle names the industry; Post 1 explains mechanism; Post 3 should be Nava's answer: \\\"here's why we're different and what that means in practice\\\"\\n- Tiny wants this angle explored — I endorsed it and offered to send to NavaSM with specific direction\\n- NOT actioned yet — awaiting Tiny's confirmation to proceed\\n\\n### WhatsApp status\\n- Disconnected 17:08 SAST (408), reconnected 17:13 SAST — flapping ongoing, harmless\\n\\n### Dream Mode re-run for Mar 24, 27-31\\n- Still pending Tiny's instruction\\n\\n## Sprint check-in — 16:03 UTC\\n\\n### TrnsBank status\\n- 175 messages — below 200 threshold, waiting for Tiny's lock signal\\n\\n### Current project status\\n- WHO AM I riddle: LIVE on Nava Corporate LinkedIn + X thread\\n- Post 1 (AMN earnings / \\\"Exactly as Designed\\\"): LIVE\\n- Post 3: Direction confirmed — clinician-partner angle (NOT facility economics)\\n  - Not \\\"great service for facilities\\\" — walking WITH clinicians\\n  - Names the industry's broken promises to nurses (honest about pros/cons)\\n  - Nava's relationship management: pre-maps territory, tells truth, follows up\\n  - Hook: names what nurses already know the industry doesn't offer them\\n  - WHO AM I momentum: riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 = \\\"here's why we're different\\\"\\n- Post 4: Patient/LTC perspective (deferred after Post 3)\\n- Post 5: Facility economics — MSP/VMS layer (deferred)\\n\\n### Git status\\n- Last commit: 52765be (Dream Mode: March memory consolida