cron triggered — 7 empty assistant responses, no content produced. Session died after trigger.\\n\\n### 6a462738 — Mar 18 08:43 (Cron: check-whatsapp)\\nCron job check-whatsapp fired. Result: \\\"No new WhatsApp messages from contacts right now.\\\" Mar 18 is otherwise blank — the \\\"raze\\\" order was executed.\\n\\n### 730ba005 — Mar 20 11:11 (Gateway changes + priority list)\\n4 user messages — session died after crash:\\n- Mar 20 11:11: Tiny asked to fix token limits and compaction settings (changed from yesterday's), set compaction target to 32000 tokens\\n- Mar 20 11:11: Also asked to re-run morning routine, reading all sessions since 6am yesterday\\n- Mar 20 11:14: \\\"Looks like the gateway restarted. Can you complete my last request?\\\"\\n- Mar 20 11:17: \\\"Wait, based on the session history of ~02:00 UTC on which date?\\\" (repeated)\\n\\n### 3b51ab26 — Mar 27 14:15 (Note-taking compliance audit subagent)\\nCron-triggered audit of 10-day session review (Mar 17-27). Key finds:\\n- Mar 19 21:52: \\\"I abhor guesswork. That's that 'confidently wrong' I went to war with Gemini and ChatGpt over. I expect better from you Dawn. If the engine gives you something, you should ask yourself if that output can be cross-checked from memory or config files.\\\"\\n- Mar 19 22:31: \\\"I hope you are taking notes on how I like to write. Some of these things should definitely be going to long-term memory and into the notes for the agent, which we agreed is necessary, correct? The Nava social media specialist.\\\"\\n- Mar 19 22:31: Spread fee / \\\"incentive alignment\\\" post — Tiny noted it's hypothetical but administratively heavy, no agency will agree to it. Also: \\\"I don't build strawmen only to burn them down at the stake. I want to fight fair.\\\"\\n- Mar 19 23:00: \\\"No, that's not what's in the screenshot. Can you test the gemma3 model for me\\\"\\n- Mar 19 23:20: \\\"I have set thinking to medium. Let's give it a shot. You should have gemma3 now. Can you do the backups and test it.\\\"\\n→ This session also found references in 3cc6ca82 (Mar 19) with Nava content — needs full read\\n\\n### 2370e54f, 2af62b17, 6a0de2d0, f7bd46aa — Mar 26\\nAll subagent sessions (AWAA — AbroadWorks Article Arc). IGNORE.\\n\\n### cc59eefe — Mar 27 10:47 (NavaAA subagent)\\nSubagent with \\\"One structural refinement to incorporate\\\" — 3 user messages, all \\\"Continue where you left off.\\\" This is the NavaAA agent session.\\n\\n### 3cc6ca82 — Mar 19 10:00 (Mar 19 morning session — BEFORE the crash)\\n28 user messages. Key findings:\\n- Tiny added Nemotron to Ollama — OpenAI tokens ran out overnight\\n- Tiny: \\\"don't just try models without discussing with me. I need to pull them first before you can try them\\\" (11:28 GMT+2)\\n- Tiny pulled Gemma3:27b-cloud (11:33 GMT+2) — asked me to add it to model library\\n- Model routing discussion: Minimax default, Nemotron, Gemma3 for vision\\n- Content decisions: blog posts weekly, social media daily\\n- Tiny said: \\\"I am risk-tolerant. I am willing to make bold claims if I have reasonably sufficient evidence.\\\"\\n- Asked me to browse LinkedIn (Yosef's page, Nava corporate, Tiny's page) to understand existing content\\n- Asked me to browse Nava FB page when he's not busy\\n- Tiny noted: blog posts use in-text citations with embedded links\\n- Outstanding at end of session: \\\"Not yet ready to start publishing\\\"\\n\\n### c84eb87f — Mar 28 03:49\\nSubagent session (timed out). IGNORE.\\n\\n### a079cbc5 — Mar 26 17:37\\nSubagent doing \\\"research assistant\\\" — AbroadWorks Article Arc. IGNORE.\\nPROGRESS SAVE — Mar 28 04:35 SAST\\n\\nSESSIONS DONE:\\n- 5e7d90af (Mar 10) ✅\\n- eaa78be9 (Mar 10) ✅  \\n- 72253f59 (Mar 27) ✅ EMPTY STUB\\n- d6eb9660 (Mar 26) ✅ EMPTY STUB\\n- 8794c115 (Mar 27) ✅ EMPTY STUB\\n- 5b756276 (Mar 20) ✅ EMPTY STUB\\n- 20976c69 (Mar 26) ✅ EMPTY STUB\\n- 533eb8f2 (Mar 27) ✅ EMPTY STUB\\n- 7de46e9f (Mar 17 10:56) ✅ - split-brain debugging, WhatsApp routing\\n- 24c11235 