we will have to raze this relay tool and rebuild it! This is what happens when you make changes without telling me!\\\"\\n- 14:57: \\\"How the fuck does this make sense? Why do you need a relay for the WSL Browser? I can't see that browser!\\\"\\n- Relay was pointing at WSL browser instead of Tiny's Windows Chrome profile\\n- Tiny had to rebuild the relay from scratch\\n- This session ends with chaos — more crashes, confusion about who Dawn is\\n- OUTCOME: Led to formalization of IDENTITY.md, memory files, and the \\\"ask first\\\" rule\\n\\n### 1cec01d5 — Mar 21 12:33 (Split-brain session)\\n5 user messages via openclaw-control-ui:\\n- \\\"I seem to be running too many sessions here, how do I close the ones I don't need?\\\"\\n- \\\"No, this is fine. My main session seems to be stuck and I don't know why.\\\"\\n- \\\"It keeps saying 'conjuring'\\\" — stuck in a loop\\n- \\\"Hold on, if you kill it, will I be able to restart it?\\\" / \\\"What happens if I just close rather than killing the session?\\\"\\n→ This is the Mar 21 split-brain crisis that was referenced in earlier sessions\\n\\n### f85a68a1 — Mar 26 19:32\\nAWAA subagent session. IGNORE.\\n\\n### 7378ca99 — Mar 27 22:00\\nCron-triggered note-taking compliance audit subagent. IGNORE (already processed).\\n\\n### a583fa6f (NavaAA agent) — Mar 25 13:09\\nNavaAA agent session stuck in restart loop:\\n- Mar 25 11:35: Tiny increased context window to 100k, updated memories\\n- NavaAA tried to use nemotron-3-super:cloud with 100k context\\n- Session KEPT failing and restarting — \\\"Continue where you left off. The previous model attempt failed or timed out.\\\"\\n- Multiple restarts (13:09, 14:15, 14:19, 14:20)\\n- Agent found: navaaa agent config at `~/.openclaw/agents/navaaa/agent/models.json`\\n- NavaAA system prompt at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/nava-writing/navaaa-system-prompt.md`\\n- Mar 25 was mainly troubleshooting the NavaAA agent setup and model transition\\n\\n## Remaining big sessions:\\n- 36da5e41 (Mar 20, 941KB) — THE ORIGINAL CRASH SESSION — this is where LI26/X18 were drafted\\n- 46e65f89 (Mar 24, 4148 lines) — Mar 24 cascade, NavaSM CustomGPT, NurseSphere article\\n- 4bc43d30 ✅ AWAA subagent\\n- da6c1677 ✅ AWAA subagent\\n\\n### 46e65f89 — Mar 24 08:32 to Mar 25 12:07 (MAR24 CASCADE — 386 user messages, 4148 lines)\\n**THIS IS THE CRITICAL SESSION.**\\n\\nTimeline:\\n- 08:32 GMT+2: \\\"Morning dawn. Run the morning brief\\\"\\n- 08:43 GMT+2: **MAJOR CONCERN** — \\\"One major concern that I have is that in the Nava blog corpus is that it has included articles I did not write. In the background, please note any articles that do not list me as the author (all my articles have a byline, 'By Tiny Manyonga'). They don't necessarily...\\\" (TRUNCATED — concern was cut off mid-sentence)\\n- 08:43 GMT+2: \\\"We are going to do the X post 001 and we are going to complete posts 002-006. More if possible, before starting on the writing lesson.\\\"\\n- 08:56 GMT+2: \\\"So kinda jumped the gun here. I don't mind that you wrote drafts for posts 001-006 here but my intention was for us to complete post001 for X first before restarting the progress on 002 that we had already made. Check the relevant session and you will see we were discussing 002 for LI first...\\\"\\n→ This confirms: I drafted all 6 posts in session context at 08:43, Tiny corrected the workflow at 08:56, but the drafts were already in session context\\n\\n**WHAT CAUSED THE CASCADE:**\\n- 09:00 SAST: Cascade started — multiple 5-min heartbeat crons fired repeatedly\\n- 09:58: \\\"Are you still there?\\\" (first of many)\\n- Each compaction = more cascade = session bloat = crash\\n- Session covers Mar 24 08:32 through Mar 25 12:07\\n\\n**KEY FINDING — LI26/X18 STATUS:**\\n- I had drafted posts 001-006 in session context\\n- At 08:56, Tiny said \\\"kinda jumped the gun\\\" — workflow correction, not deletion\\n- The drafts existed in session context when cascade hit\\n- They were NEVER saved to file\\n-