i`\\n- Date: `Mon 2026-04-06 15:24 GMT+2`\\n\\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Mon 2026-04-06 15:14 GMT+2] Yeah, take a shot at my personal post.\\n- Assistant: When I was leading SDR teams, growth was the only metric that moved the needle. We lived for the \\\"up and to the right\\\" trajectory. If revenue was climbing, everyone was happy. Growth, by definition, was the goal.\\n\\nBut since moving into healthcare strategy at Nava, I've had to reconsider what growth actually signals. In a sales funnel, growth is a victory. In an oncology ward, it is a diagnosis.\\n\\nThe travel nursing market is usually quoted at $39 billion. But that number doesn't tell you anything without the frame. In 2019, it was a $6.5 billion niche. Today, even after the post-pandemic correc...\\n- User: Pre-compaction memory flush. Store durable memories only in memory/2026-04-06.md (create memory/ if needed). Treat workspace bootstrap/reference files such as MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, and AGENTS.md as read-only during this flush; never overwrite, replace, or edit them. If memory/2026-04-06.md already exists, APPEND new content only and do not overwrite existing entries. Do NOT create timestamped variant files (e.g., 2026-04-06-HHMM.md); always use the canonical 2026-04-06.md filename. If nothing to store, reply with NO_REPLY.\\nCurrent time: Monday, April 6th, 2026 — 3:18 PM (Africa/Johanne...\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (read): # 2026-04-06 — Session Log\\n\\n## Dusk VPS — Setup & Access\\n\\n### Gateway Status\\n- Dusk's gateway was DEAD for ~6 hours (10:49 UTC, crashed after WhatsApp conflict)\\n- Restarted successfully: `systemctl --user start openclaw-gateway`\\n- Running on: `0.0.0.0:18789` (publicly accessible with token)\\n- Token: `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2`\\n\\n### Ports found on Dusk\\n- `18789` — Gateway WebSocket (0.0.0.0)\\n- `18791` — Control UI (localhost only)\\n- `80/443` — Caddy web server (proxies to gateway)\\n\\n### Caddyfile (Dusk)\\n```\\n:80 { reverse_proxy localhost:18789 }\\n:443 { reverse_proxy localhost:18789 }\\n```\\n→ If ...\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-06.md.\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (exec): [master 409b911] Apr 6 afternoon: Post 1 live, NavaSM rewritten, market data, personal post draft, screenshot path fixed\\n 1 file changed, 74 insertions(+)\\n- Assistant: NO_REPLY\\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Mon 2026-04-06 15:18 GMT+2] Where is $25 b coming from? and we are missing the projection. I would put it towards the end.\\n- Assistant: You're right on both counts.\\n\\n**On $25B:** I pulled it from the CustomGPT session, which stated it as fact without showing its work. I didn't verify it against a named source before using it. That's lazy — and worse, it's exactly the kind of unverified number you'd call out in my own writing.\\n\\n**On the projection:** I had $90 billion by 2033 from the CustomGPT session (total healthcare staffing market), but I left it out of the draft. It belongs in the final version.\\n\\nLet me check what sources we actually have for these numbers before I revise.\\n[non-text content: toolCall x2]\\n- Tool result (exec): /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/clean_txt/2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md:Travel nursing is now a permanent feature of American healthcare, not a crisis response. The market hit $39 billion last year. It's projected to reach $72 billion by 2033. That growth isn't a sign the system is solving its staffing problem, but a symptom the system is more dependent on the thing causing the problem.\\n- Tool result (exec): /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md:Travel nursing is now a permanent feature of American healthcare, not a crisis response. The market hit $39 billion last year. It's projected to reach $72 billion by 2033. That growth isn't a sign the system is solving its staffing problem, but a symptom the system is more dependent on the thing causing the problem.\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md:- Market size ($39B → $72B): Travel Nursing Market Size, Growth, Scope & Forecast Report - 2033, beckershospitalreview.com\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall x2]\\n- Tool result (exec): /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/clean_txt/10_navahc_com_healthcare_reputation_management.txt:The patient-facing failures detailed above are merely lagging indicators, the tell-tale signs of a failure in recruitment and coordination. They are the symptoms. Among the root causes of these failures is the collapse of the organization&#8217;s employer-facing reputation. This is the central, misunderstood component of healthcare reputation management: 2023-2025 data proves these internal workforce failures are the leading (predicting) indicators of a future patient experience crisis. If a he...\\n- Tool result (web_search): {\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"travel nursing market size 2024 current billion current state\\\",\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"brave\\\",\\n  \\\"count\\\": 5,\\n  \\\"tookMs\\\": 2104,\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_search\\\",\\n    \\\"provider\\\": \\\"brave\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"results\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"e1761575db915093\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\n18+ Travel Nursing Statistics & Trends for 2025 | Betternurse.org\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"e1761575db915093\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://betternurse.org/travel-nursing-statistics/\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"\\\\n...\\n- Assistant: Verified. Here's what I found:\\n\\n- **2019:** $6.5 billion (pre-pandemic baseline) — confirmed\\n- **2022:** $42.7 billion (pandemic peak) — confirmed\\n- **2023:** $25.2 billion (post-correction, \\\"new normal\\\") — confirmed\\n- **2024:** $39.46 billion (current) — confirmed\\n- **2033 projection:** $71.81 billion — confirmed\\n\\nThe $25B figure checks out — it's the 2023 post-correction number from Staffing Industry Analysts (SIA). The CustomGPT's $44.6B was close to the actual $42.7B. The projection numbers were also in the right ballpark.\\n\\nThe key insight holds: even after the 40% contraction from peak, w...\\n\\n<read-files>\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-25.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-28-blog-corpus-audit.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-05.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/transcript-mining/00_COMPREHENSIVE_READ.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-linkedin-series/POST-1-draft.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/nava-writing/navasm-system-prompt.md\\n/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-04-06 143040.png\\n\\n</read-files>\\n\\n<modified-files>\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-06.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/morning_routine_state.json\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/clean_txt/2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/navasm/SKILL.md\\n\\n</modified-files>\",\"firstKeptEntryId\":\"6a174112\",\"tokensBefore\":80305,\"details\":{\"readFiles\":[\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-25.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-28-blog-corpus-audit.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-05.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/transcript-mining/00_COMPREHENSIVE_READ.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-linkedin-series/POST-1-draft.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/nava-writing/navasm-system-prompt.md\",\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-04-06 143040.png\"],\"modifiedFiles\":[\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-06.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/morning_routine_state.json\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/clean_txt/2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md\",\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/navasm/SKILL.md\"]},\"fromHook\":true}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"b0cbf0e1\",\"parentId\":\"c32a9fe4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-06T18:42:05.117Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Mon 2026-04-06 20:41 GMT+2] So this post is good but it's for the Nava page. I don't think using \\\"I\\\" is appropriate here. What do you think?\"}],\"timestamp\":1775500925106}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"8fa45297\",\"parentId\":\"b0cbf0e1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-06T18:42:23.635Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"You're right. \\\"I\\\" on the Nava Corporate page is wrong — it implies the CEO or a specific person speaking, not the company. Corporate page should be \\\"we.\\\"\\n\\nThe structure is good but the voice needs to shift. Something like:\\n\\n> There's a nurse we keep thinking about.\\n\\nOr drop the first-person entirely and go observational:\\n\\n> Eight patients. One CNA. On an oncology floor.\\n\\n> The nurse who went into this work because she wanted to help people. Managing eight chemotherapy patients overnight with one aide, because somewhere a spreadsheet decided that was an acceptable number.\\n\\n> The person who couldn't press the call light fast enough. The family who waited forty minutes for someone to help their mother to the bathroom. The nurse who went home knowing she missed something she should have caught.\\n\\n> This isn't a shortage problem. It's a business model problem.\\n\\n> The travel nursing industry was a $6.5 billion niche in 2019. Today it's $25 billion. By 2033 it's heading toward $72 billion. That money isn't fixing healthcare. It's profitable off the fact that healthcare keeps needing it.\\n\\n> We wrote about why this keeps happening — and what it would actually take to change the math.\\n\\nWant me to update the file with the corrected data and corporate voice?\"}],\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.7:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":44707,\"output\":606,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":45313,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1775500943633}}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":115,"aggregated":"{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"249fb34c\",\"parentId\":\"6374a1a4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-06T12:05:07.143Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_6c9d6cf0-3043-44bd-b304-715d09584b96\",\"toolName\":\"web_search\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"travel nurse pay vs permanent nurse sala