ext)\\n- $72B projected by 2033\\n- Key framing terms: \\\"State Change,\\\" \\\"Acuity Gap,\\\" \\\"Arbitrage Premium,\\\" \\\"Acuity-Based Staffing\\\"\\n\\n**CNA ratios by unit:**\\n- Med-Surg: 1:10-1:12 crisis\\n- Oncology: 1:8 crisis\\n- LTC: 1:20-1:30 crisis\\n- Rehab: 1:15 crisis\\n- ED: 1:20+ crisis\\n\\n**Cost figures (lawyer-corrected):**\\n- TN: $7,000-$15,000 all-in\\n- EB-3: $25,000-$35,000 all-in\\n\\n**Global aging data:**\\n- 1 in 6 over 60 by 2030\\n\\n**Travel nurse pay data (Vivian, Dec 2024):**\\n- Staff: $1,814/week\\n- Travel: $2,294/week (~26% premium, NOT double pay)\\n\\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\\n\\n## Decisions\\n- No decisions made yet.\\n\\n## Open TODOs\\n- Add the latest screenshot (Screenshot 2026-04-06 152420.png) to the corpus as requested by the user.\\n\\n## Constraints/Rules\\n- (none)\\n\\n## Pending user asks\\n- User wants the latest screenshot added to the corpus.\\n\\n## Exact identifiers\\n- Latest screenshot: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-04-06 152420.png`\\n- Earlier screenshots found:\\n  - `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-04-06 143040.png`\\n  - `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-04-06 144532.png`\\n- Sender label: `openclaw-tui (gateway-client)`\\n- Sender ID: `gateway-client`\\n- Sender name/username: `openclaw-tui`\\n- Date: `Mon 2026-04-06 15:24 GMT+2`\\n\\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Mon 2026-04-06 15:14 GMT+2] Yeah, take a shot at my personal post.\\n- Assistant: When I was leading SDR teams, growth was the only metric that moved the needle. We lived for the \\\"up and to the right\\\" trajectory. If revenue was climbing, everyone was happy. Growth, by definition, was the goal.\\n\\nBut since moving into healthcare strategy at Nava, I've had to reconsider what growth actually signals. In a sales funnel, growth is a victory. In an oncology ward, it is a diagnosis.\\n\\nThe travel nursing market is usually quoted at $39 billion. But that number doesn't tell you anything without the frame. In 2019, it was a $6.5 billion niche. Today, even after the post-pandemic correc...\\n- User: Pre-compaction memory flush. Store durable memories only in memory/2026-04-06.md (create memory/ if needed). Treat workspace bootstrap/reference files such as MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, and AGENTS.md as read-only during this flush; never overwrite, replace, or edit them. If memory/2026-04-06.md already exists, APPEND new content only and do not overwrite existing entries. Do NOT create timestamped variant files (e.g., 2026-04-06-HHMM.md); always use the canonical 2026-04-06.md filename. If nothing to store, reply with NO_REPLY.\\nCurrent time: Monday, April 6th, 2026 — 3:18 PM (Africa/Johanne...\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (read): # 2026-04-06 — Session Log\\n\\n## Dusk VPS — Setup & Access\\n\\n### Gateway Status\\n- Dusk's gateway was DEAD for ~6 hours (10:49 UTC, crashed after WhatsApp conflict)\\n- Restarted successfully: `systemctl --user start openclaw-gateway`\\n- Running on: `0.0.0.0:18789` (publicly accessible with token)\\n- Token: `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2`\\n\\n### Ports found on Dusk\\n- `18789` — Gateway WebSocket (0.0.0.0)\\n- `18791` — Control UI (localhost only)\\n- `80/443` — Caddy web server (proxies to gateway)\\n\\n### Caddyfile (Dusk)\\n```\\n:80 { reverse_proxy localhost:18789 }\\n:443 { reverse_proxy localhost:18789 }\\n```\\n→ If ...\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-06.md.\\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (exec): [master 40