light fast enough. The family who waited forty minutes for someone to help their mother to the bathroom. The nurse who went home knowing she missed something she should have caught.\\n\\n> This isn't a shortage problem. It's a business model problem.\\n\\n> The travel nursing industry was a $6.5 billion niche in 2019. Today it's $25 billion. By 2033 it's heading toward $72 billion. That money isn't fixing healthcare. It's profitable off the fact that healthcare keeps needing it.\\n\\n> We wrote about why this keeps happening — and what it would actually take to change the math.\\n\\nWant me to update the file with the corrected data and corporate voice?\"}],\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.7:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":44707,\"output\":606,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":45313,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1775500943633}}","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775740662667}}
