{"type":"message","id":"c7157500","parentId":"ef3a0bb4","timestamp":"2026-04-09T13:25:23.392Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_a9b07c6f-fc12-49f3-9657-9511ffa6650a","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Draft an X (Twitter) version of Post 3 — the continuity/merry-go-round post.\n\n**Post 3 core:**\nA nurse reaches week seven — knows the culture, the karaoke spots. Week thirteen, they're gone. The 13-week exit isn't random. Familiarity breeds discomfort for agencies — a nurse who knows your unit is harder to place. So the system moves them before they feel at home. Units absorb handoff errors, orientation costs, institutional knowledge that never accumulates. Nava's answer: truth at placement, follow-up after arrival, relationships that outlast the contract. \"Because we don't deal in 13-week merry-go-rounds.\"\n\n**Task:**\n1. Consider: single tweet vs 2-tweet thread\n2. The karaoke detail is the best concrete hook — use it\n3. Bold works in X for emphasis\n4. Aim for the minimum number of tweets needed to tell the full story\n5. End with \"merry-go-rounds\" as the contrast word\n6. Max 280 chars per tweet\n\n**Output:** Draft version(s) — 1-tweet and/or 2-tweet options. No preamble.","runtime":"subagent"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":77711,"output":1483,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79194,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775741123390}}
