{"type":"message","id":"e0d4ae3d","parentId":"24ac4303","timestamp":"2026-04-09T13:29:24.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"NavaSM is back with options. Running through TinyQE now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_50b7a8db-be48-4c17-8f19-d2cfcc38dd5d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && python3 -c \"\nfrom tinyqe.tinyqe import TinyQE\n\ntqe = TinyQE()\n\n# Option 1: single tweet\no1 = 'By week seven, a nurse knows your unit'\\''s rhythm — the shorthand, the good coffee, the karaoke spot after shift. Week thirteen: they'\\''re gone. The 13-week exit isn'\\''t random. A nurse who knows your unit is harder to place. We don'\\''t do 13-week merry-go-rounds.'\n\n# Option 2: thread\nt1 = 'Week 7: knows the culture, the charge nurse'\\''s shorthand, the karaoke spot after shift. Week 13: they'\\''re gone. The 13-week exit isn'\\''t a bug — it'\\''s a feature.'\nt2 = 'Agencies move nurses before they feel at home. Easier to place someone who doesn'\\''t know your unit yet. Truth at placement. Follow-up after arrival. We don'\\''t do 13-week merry-go-rounds.'\n\nprint('=== OPTION 1 (single tweet) ===')\nprint(o1)\nprint()\nr1 = tqe.evaluate(o1, 'x')\nfor dim, score in r1.dimension_scores.items():\n    print(f'  {dim}: {score}')\nprint(f'  OVERALL: {r1.overall_score}/100')\nprint()\n\nprint('=== OPTION 2 (2-tweet thread) ===')\nprint('Tweet 1:', t1)\nprint('Tweet 2:', t2)\nprint()\nr2a = tqe.evaluate(t1, 'x')\nr2b = tqe.evaluate(t2, 'x')\nfor label, r in [('Tweet 1', r2a), ('Tweet 2', r2b)]:\n    print(f'  {label} overall: {r.overall_score}/100')\n\"\n"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":24377,"output":667,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25044,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775741364310}}
