{"type":"message","id":"0743d14d","parentId":"bf500969","timestamp":"2026-04-09T13:30:57.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TinyQE done. Scores are close — 0.481 vs 0.458/0.475. Both weak on flow and evidence, which is expected for X posts (TinyQE was built for long-form). Here's my read:\n\n**Option 1 (single tweet)** — 280 chars, one hit\n> By week seven, a nurse knows your unit's rhythm — the shorthand, the good coffee, the karaoke spot after shift. Week thirteen: they're gone. The 13-week exit isn't random. A nurse who knows your unit is harder to place. **We don't do 13-week merry-go-rounds.**\n\n**Option 2 (2-tweet thread)** — the \"feature not a bug\" reveal\n> **Tweet 1:** Week 7: knows the culture, the charge nurse's shorthand, the karaoke spot after shift. Week 13: they're gone. The 13-week exit isn't a bug — it's a feature.\n>\n> **Tweet 2:** Agencies move nurses before they feel at home. Easier to place someone who doesn't know your unit yet. Truth at placement. Follow-up after arrival. **We don't do 13-week merry-go-rounds.**\n\n**My recommendation: Option 2.**\nThe \"feature not a bug\" line is the intellectual hook — it makes the reader stop and recalibrate. That moment of recalibration is what separates X posts that get screenshot-saved from ones that scroll past. The karaoke detail carries Tweet 1, the mechanism carries Tweet 2. Two tweets earn the closer.\n\nOption 1 is good. Option 2 is the move.\n\nWhich do you want to publish?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":29024,"output":814,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29838,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775741457568}}
