{"type":"message","id":"e82cfb88","parentId":"c070edfb","timestamp":"2026-04-09T13:44:12.081Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_dfb515c4-5779-4273-a1e8-2e2fa1940e70","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-04-09\n\n## Dream Mode — Nightly Reflection (Apr 8 → Apr 9)\n\n### Session Reviewed: April 8, 2026\n\n---\n\n## Key Events from April 8\n\n### WHO AM I Riddle — Built and Posted\n- Developed in real-time during session (10:23-12:44 UTC)\n- Final 3-clue structure:\n  1. \"I am a consistent contributor to short-term rental leases across the US, but I do not own property.\" — proptech/landlord misdirect\n  2. \"My experts are brought in at a premium to cover problems your organisation should be able to handle, then disappear a few months later.\" — consulting misdirect\n  3. \"Your workers' strike is a delight for my investors, even when lives are at stake.\" — narrows to predatory staffing\n- Image posted to Nava Corporate LinkedIn — confirmed LIVE\n- X thread: 4 tweets co-created (Tiny wrote Tweet 2-4 himself)\n- FB post: combined Tiny's edits + NavaSM iteration\n\n### NavaSM Editorial Protocol — Established\n- Tiny's correction: NavaSM generates → I EDIT → present to Tiny\n- NEVER pass through raw output\n- Must apply editorial judgment: tone consistency, rhythm, closer landing, energy match\n- Use TinyQE for dimensional scoring if uncertain\n- NavaSM is a creative partner, not a transcription service\n\n### Post 3 Direction Confirmed — Clinician-Partner Angle\n- Tiny's reframe: Nava's value is not just \"great service for facilities\" — it's walking WITH clinicians\n- We know the complaints: no truth about units, no follow-up, contract exploitation\n- We know the pros/cons of travel (honest accounting)\n- We do relationship management differently: pre-map territory, tell truth, follow up, continuity compounds\n- Sequence: clinician → patient → facility economics (Post 3 → 4 → 5)\n- WHO AM I momentum: riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 = \"here's why we're different\"\n\n### Dream Mode Run (Overnight Mar 16-31)\n- 16 daily files processed\n- Issues: Mar 24 (3.1MB session) underprocessed; Mar 27-31 not done\n- Committed: 52765be\n\n### \"? = Nudge\" Hard Rule — Reinforced\n- Solitary \"?\" = nudge only, never interpret as question or call to action\n- Never take unilateral steps on \"?\"\n- TUI shows idle during background work — Tiny cannot see what I'm doing\n\n### TrnsBank Status\n- 175/200 — waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n- Not actionable until he signals ready\n\n---\n\n## Current Project Status\n\n| Project | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| WHO AM I riddle | LIVE on Nava Corporate LI + X thread |\n| Post 1 (Exactly as Designed) | LIVE |\n| Post 3 | Direction confirmed — clinician-partner angle, awaiting Tiny's go-ahead |\n| Post 4 | Patient/LTC perspective (deferred after Post 3) |\n| Post 5 | Facility economics — MSP/VMS layer (deferred) |\n| TrnsBank | 175/200, waiting lock signal |\n| Dream Mode Mar 24, 27-31 | Needs re-run |\n| TinyQE B1/B2 fix | Pending — needs 30-min dedicated session |\n| CustomGPT v5 HTML files | Still Windows-only, inaccessible |\n\n---\n\n## Nava Content Arc (as of Apr 8)\n\n1. ~~Post 1: Exactly as Designed (AMN earnings / labor disruption revenue)~~ — LIVE\n2. ~~WHO AM I riddle (hook/entry point)~~ — LIVE Apr 8\n3. Post 3: Clinician-partner angle — **READY TO BUILD** (pending Tiny's go-ahead)\n4. Post 4: Patient/LTC perspective — deferred\n5. Post 5: Facility economics (MSP/VMS layer, KPMG \"$89 vs $94\" frame) — deferred\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Apr 8\n\n1. **Post 3 = clinician experience, NOT facility economics** — clinician perspective first, patient second, facility third\n2. **NavaSM editorial protocol** — I edit before presenting, never pass through raw\n3. **WHO AM I answer mechanism** — riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 is the earned answer\n\n---\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Tiny writes better tweets than I do** — Tweet 2-4 from Apr 8 were Tiny's own; my drafts were \"dead giveaways\"\n2. **NavaSM prompts need specificity** — thin context = weak output; specific direction = usable draft\n3. **WHO AM I works as engagement mechanism** — the 3-clue image + X thread drove curiosity loop\n\n---\n\n## Open TODOs (carried forward)\n\n- [ ] Post 3 clinician-partner — awaiting Tiny's go-ahead\n- [ ] Re-run Dream Mode for Mar 24, 27-31\n- [ ] TrnsBank at 175/200 — wait for lock signal\n- [ ] TinyQE B1/B2 fix — 30-min dedicated session needed\n- [ ] CustomGPT HTML files — need Windows running\n\n[177 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775742252056}}
