ed to assign categories/structure as discussed last week]\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/customer-service/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/demand-shift/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/development-and-ai/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/digital-marketing/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/englishproficiency/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/eor/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/faq/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/federal-reserve/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/interview-tips/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/legal/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/manage-remote-team/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/offshore-accountant/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/offshore-accounting/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/offshore-labor-future/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/offshore-risks/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/offshorephva/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/outsourcing-to-the-philippines-a-smart-move-for-business-growth/\n\n2. Title tag\nGoal : SERP Snippet + CTR [SERP : Search Engine Results Page]\nExpectation:\n• Unique for every page.\n• Includes primary keyword near the beginning.\n• Between 50-60 characters.\n• Clear, compelling, and relevant to the page content.\n• Important for SERP Snippet and high CTRs\nExisting : Good\nUrl\n\nTitles\n\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/customer-service/\n\nHire a Customer Service Agent - AbroadWorks\n\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/demand-shift/\n\nRising Worker Demands and the Offshore Shift - AbroadWorks\n--\n5. Header tags hierarchy (H2, H3…)\nGoal : User Readability\nExpectation\n• Logical use of heading structure (<h2>, <h3>, etc.).\n• Include secondary keywords where appropriate.\n• Helps break content into readable sections.\nDuplicate H2s\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/virtual-assistant/\nhttps://www.abroadworks.com/digital-marketing/\n\n6. Content Quality\nGoal : User Engagement\nExpectation\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n\nUnique and original content (not duplicated from other sites).\nWords per page > those of top 5 competitors for the target keyword\nWell-written, grammatically correct, and useful to users.\nIncludes primary and related (LSI) keywords naturally.\nNo keyword stuffing.\nMore in Content Strategy later in this document.\n\n7. Image Optimizations\nGoal : Page Speed + User Experience\nExpectation\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n\nAll images should have descriptive alt tags.\nimage names should be keyword-relevant (seo-audit-checklist.png).\nImage file size optimized for fast loading.\nModify the render of image differently for desktop/ mobiles based on the screen width\nUse of modern formats like WebP\nSize should be between 10kb to 100kb (max).\n\nExisting : Many images are above 100kb\n\n8. Internal Linking\nGoal : User Engagement + Efficient Crawling & Indexing\nExpectation\n•\n•\n--\n14. Keyword Targeting\nGoal : Search Intent Fulfillment + Page Ranking\nExpectation\n•\n•\n\n•\n\nClear keyword intent (informational, transactional, etc.).\nKeyword appears in:\n§ Title,\n§ H1,\n§ Meta description,\n§ First 100 words,\n§ Image alt text,\n§ URL.\nMore in Content Strategy later in this document.\n\n15. Social Sharing Optimization\nGoal : Page Sharing + Virality\nExpectation\n•\n•\n\nOpen Graph tags (og:title, og:image, etc.).\nShare buttons available (if applicable).\n\nExisting : Good\nExample url : https://www.abroadworks.com/digital-marketing/\n\n16. On-Page Content Creation Strategy with an Example\nExisting URL : https://www.abroadworks.com/offshorephva/\nKeyword: hire a virtual assistant in the Philippines\nURL slug: /blog/hire-virtual-assistant-philippines","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775759492909}}
