ppines\nHow to hire a VA in the Philippines\n\nWord Count: 2,000–3,000 [Should be greater than the top 5 pages ranking for this phrase]\nArticle Title [H1]:\nHow to Hire a Virtual Assistant in the Philippines: Complete Guide\nSEO Optimization Checklist:\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n•\n\nEach LSI keyword mentioned 2–7 times\nUse at least one LSI keyword in an H2 heading\n2–5+ outbound links to credible sources (e.g., Upwork, OnlineJobs.ph)\n5–15+ internal links to relevant articles (e.g., productivity tools, remote team hiring, etc.)\nKeyword included in meta description\nKeyword in H1 title\nKeyword in at least one H2 heading\nPage title between 35–65 characters\nURL slug is short and includes the keyword\nEnsure the topic hasn’t been published on the blog before\nAdd featured image (under H1) and images under all H2 titles\nLimit to 2–4 lines per paragraph.\n\nEnhancements for Better Engagement\n•\n•\n•\n\n•\n•\n•\n•\n\nCreate a youtube video and link it (under H1) to be clickable on the featured image.\no Make it to load in a popup for better page speed\nUse Bullet Points and Numbered Lists\no Ideal for step-by-step processes, tools, or benefits.\nHighlight Key Information\no Bold key terms, phrases, or takeaways.Use italics for emphasis or tone.\no Use quote blocks or callout boxes for definitions or notes.\nUse Visual Aids\no Add screenshots, infographics, charts, or icons.\nInclude a Table of Contents (for long posts)\no Helps users jump to relevant sections. Improves navigation and time on page.\nAdd Structured Schema for better google profiling\nLLM readability – LLMS.txt / Agents.txt [TBD]\n\n17. On-Page Content Outline Framework with an Example\nExisting URL: https://www.abroadworks.com/offshorephva/\nKeyword: hire a virtual assistant in the Philippines\nIntroduction (0 - 100 words)\nExplain the growing need for remote support and why hiring a virtual assistant in the Philippines is a smart"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2