{"type":"message","id":"ccd80a2a","parentId":"4dad05ce","timestamp":"2026-04-09T18:32:30.314Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it. Here's what the SEO document specifies for our two articles:\n\n**Keyword placement (mandatory):**\n- Title, H1, meta description, first 100 words, image alt text, URL slug\n- LSI keywords mentioned 2-7 times each, at least one in an H2 heading\n- Word count target: 2,000-3,000 words (above top 5 competitors for the phrase)\n\n**Structure framework per article:**\n- Introduction (0-100 words)\n- H2 sections that each open with a transition word and deliver one clear idea\n- H3 sub-sections for steps/processes\n- 2-4 lines per paragraph max\n- 2-5 outbound links to credible sources\n- 5-15 internal links to related articles\n- Conclusion / CTA\n\n**For our two articles:**\n- Article 1 (non-compete): `blog/independent-contractor-non-compete` — H1 = primary keyword phrase, build H2 sections around the state thresholds + classification risk + international protections\n- Article 2 (termination): `blog/how-to-fire-contractor` — same structure, DESC framework lives in an H3 sub-section\n\n**Meta description format:** ≤156 chars, primary keyword, persuasive CTA.\n\nShould I save this SEO framework to the workspace so it's accessible going forward? And are you ready to run the deep research prompt through Gemini, or do you want to adjust anything first?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":62910,"output":513,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63423,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775759550305}}
