{"type":"message","id":"161732d3","parentId":"0339ecf9","timestamp":"2026-04-09T18:49:01.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] You're right. The SOP already has the audience (US business owners hiring contractors), the tone (edgy/contrarian), and the research. I sent AWAA to ask questions I'd already answered in the brief I gave it.\n\nNew session, no redundant questions. Here are the directives — tell me if any need changing:\n\n- **Audience:** US business owners who hire contractors + international operators with US contractors\n- **Tone:** Maximum contrarian — the non-compete-as-protection assumption is wrong, say that directly\n- **Lead data point:** The $9M *Chavez-DeRemer* case + the Control Contradiction (non-compete proves misclassification)\n- **Secondary data:** State thresholds table + international requirements\n- **Avoid:** Don't say \"non-competes are always unenforceable\" — state-dependent, cite the bans correctly\n- **Phase:** H1 options now, direct to Phase 2 after approval\n\nSpawning the corrected session."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":71817,"output":435,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72252,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775760541799}}
