{"type":"message","id":"952c1267","parentId":"116190dd","timestamp":"2026-04-09T18:59:32.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] `independent contractor non-compete` — it's the URL slug from the keyword document.\n\nBut you're making a good point. That keyword is an SEO targeting play — someone googling that exact phrase is likely mid-funnel, already considering the question. The micro-business owner audience probably isn't searching that phrase. They're searching \"do contractors need non-compete\" or \"contractor non-compete\" or \"independent contractor agreement what to include.\"\n\nThe keyword gets us found. The angle keeps them reading. Those are two different jobs.\n\nShould I tell AWAA to optimize for the longer-tail question-based keyword variants while keeping `independent contractor non-compete` in the H1 and intro for SEO? Or keep the exact-match keyword in the H1 and trust the angle to carry the educational value?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":75321,"output":429,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75750,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775761172349}}
