{"type":"message","id":"7f47e3fb","parentId":"2c6c4b24","timestamp":"2026-04-09T20:16:52.886Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_e72e493d-eff6-435a-b9a8-dc4243470b30","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-03.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 276,\n      \"endLine\": 310,\n      \"score\": 0.41620299220085144,\n      \"snippet\": \"7. **Dream mode**: \\\"Research dream mode, I think Anthropic AI does it\\\" at 22:50. — **Set up pending Tiny confirmation.**\\n\\n### Python Extraction Note (for future)\\nThe correct way to extract Tiny's messages from a session .reset file:\\n```python\\nimport json\\nwith open(reset_file) as f:\\n    for line in f:\\n        data = json.loads(line)\\n        if data['type'] == 'message' and data['message']['role'] == 'user':\\n            # parse content[0]['text']\\n            # skip Conversation info wrappers, system messages, cron events\\n            # extract lines starting with [Thu/[Fri etc\\n```\\n\\nFilter: skip text < 50 chars, skip 'Conversation info', 'Sender (untrusted', 'Sprint check-in', 'Pre-compaction',\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-03.md#L276-L310\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-03.md#L276-L310\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 744,\n      \"endLine\": 778,\n      \"score\": 0.4135246306657791,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Files: `tinyqe/` directory with brief, framework, CLI, core modules, analyzers, format profiles, glossaries\\n\\n## NavaSM Agent — Planned\\n\\n**Purpose:** Autonomous LinkedIn/X poster for Nava Healthcare\\n**Not yet built.** Will be created after Post 002-006 cycle.\\n**Why separate:** Different voice, different goals from Tiny's personal content\\n\\n## Dusk VPS (LightningBugIV) — Setup Complete Apr 5\\n\\n**Purpose:** Cloud backup/secondary instance of OpenClaw\\n**IP:** 204.168.204.198 (Hetzner CX22, Ubuntu 24.04, 2 vCPU, 3.7GB RAM)\\n\\n**Access methods:**\\n- Gateway: `ws://204.168.204.198:18789` (token: `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2`)\\n- TUI: SSH tunnel required — `ssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 Tiny4Lurv@204\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L744-L778\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L744-L778\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 888,\n      \"endLine\": 896,\n      \"score\": 0.4115891307592392,\n      \"snippet\": \"## CustomGPT v5 Files — BLOCKED (4th mention, unresolved)\\n\\n**Files:** `NewGemini.html` (6.8MB), `HumanizedGemini.html` (7.1MB)\\n**Location:** Windows Downloads (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Tiny4Lurv\\\\Downloads\\\\`)\\n**Purpose:** Editorial skill input for Nava writing\\n**Problem:** Windows files not accessible from WSL without Windows running + WSLg active\\n**Status:** Referenced Mar 28, Apr 2, Apr 3 — still unread\\n**Action:** Need Windows running to access\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L888-L896\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L888-L896\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/transcript-mining/00_COMPREHENSIVE_READ.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 428,\n      \"endLine\": 471,\n      \"score\": 0.40941887497901913,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Currently deferred in allowlist\\n\\n**PEOPLE MENTIONED:**\\n- Ncami (Tiny's girlfriend?)\\n- Betsho (possibly another relationship)\\n- Dean (someone I was initially set up with on Mar 10)\\n\\n**TONES HE USED:**\\n- Impatient when I miss obvious things (\\\"Dude, installing Chrome...\\\")\\n- Dark humor (\\\"Fuck, that did not work. Let's Raze the session stuff\\\")\\n- Direct (\\\"Burn down what you need to burn down\\\")\\n- Playful (\\\"I love both Ncami and Betsho\\\" was a test message)\\n- Serious about Digital Twin project\\n\\n**WHAT TINY GAVE ME TO READ (Mar 17):**\\n- Nava documents (placed in workspace)\\n- ChatGPT \\\"Agent Mode Explanation\\\" conversation\\n- LinkedIn access via relay\\n\\n**AT SESSION END (12:33 GMT+2):**\\n- WhatsA