{"type":"message","id":"3ef110a1","parentId":"b1ee9d52","timestamp":"2026-04-09T20:20:43.201Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Let me back up.\n\nOpenClaw has two things that look like \"dashboards\":\n\n1. **The Control UI** — the gateway management interface at port 18789. You use it to configure agents, channels, crons. It's administrative, not conversational. This is what you're landing on now.\n\n2. **The webchat** — the conversational interface. That's what you're using in the TUI right now, or what you'd access at a dedicated URL if we set up a web-accessible chat endpoint.\n\nRight now on Dusk, only the Control UI (gateway) is exposed. There is no webchat endpoint running on Dusk that lets you chat with me through a browser.\n\nWhat Dusk could help you build is exactly that — a lightweight web page that connects to the OpenClaw gateway and lets you chat. That's the webapp idea. The gateway is already there; the webchat frontend is what doesn't exist yet.\n\nSo: you're at the right place asking the right question. They should be able to tell you what's needed to host a simple webchat client that connects to `ws://204.168.204.198:18789`."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":50146,"output":430,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775766043193}}
