{"type":"message","id":"0c2a9cbb","parentId":"6fe965a1","timestamp":"2026-04-09T20:22:17.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n[[reply_to_current]] You can. That's a different tool — not OpenClaw, a terminal-over-HTTP server.\n\nOptions for Dusk:\n\n1. **Shell in a Box** — runs a terminal in a browser window\n2. **GoTTY** — shares the TUI over HTTP\n3. **Cockpit** — already installed at `https://204.168.204.198:9090` (web-based server management that includes a terminal)\n\nCockpit is already there. Log in with your Dusk credentials and look for the Terminal option in the menu. That's your Ubuntu TUI in a browser.\n\nIf Cockpit's terminal isn't visible or doesn't work, `shellinabox` or `gotty` would do the job — ask Dusk to install one of those."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":51187,"output":293,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51480,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775766137253}}
