{"type":"message","id":"c2a5eaca","parentId":"0354e0aa","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:02:05.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Honest answer: somewhere in between.\n\n**What will work:**\n- Facts are right, sourced correctly\n- Structure is solid — the Problem/Agitation/Solution arc is correct\n- Word count is there\n- No em-dashes, no self-references, no banned terms\n\n**What you'll hate:**\n- Vocabulary is generic. Every sentence uses the predictable word. \"Contractor\" where a more specific word earns the point. \"Protecting\" where \"shielding\" is more precise to the context. It reads technically correct but flat.\n- Transitions are functional, not earned. The jump from one point to the next is bridged correctly, but the bridge is boring.\n- The emotional texture is missing. Your writing has texture. AWAA's drafts don't.\n\nYou taught me the patterns. These drafts have the opposite of those patterns baked in. You'll feel the difference the second you open them. That's actually good — you'll know exactly what to fix, and your corrections will be fast. The structural work is done. Your pass is the creative work.\n\nShitshow? No. Frustrating draft that needs your specific voice inserted into it? Yes."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":62864,"output":557,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63421,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775768525019}}
