{"type":"message","id":"f1fcd4e3","parentId":"408557da","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:04:17.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n[[reply_to_current]] No — Ollama is a local LLM runtime. It runs models on the machine it's installed on. It has nothing to do with OpenClaw gateway authentication.\n\nThe 401 error was about the gateway token not being set. Dusk advised you to export the token before running `openclaw` commands — that was the fix, not Ollama.\n\nIf you're still getting 401 after running:\n```\nexport OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2\n```\nthen the issue is either:\n1. The token value itself is wrong on Dusk's config\n2. The gateway on Dusk is running with different credentials than what's in MEMORY.md\n\nCheck what token Dusk actually has by running `openclaw config get gateway.token` on the VPS. If it doesn't match `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2`, that's your answer."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":63283,"output":404,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63687,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775768657002}}
