{"type":"message","id":"5cba4096","parentId":"2cf4449f","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:08:34.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] That's expected — OpenClaw redacts tokens in config output. The fact that it shows `__OPENCLAW_REDACTED__` (not \"field not found\") means the token **is configured** on Dusk. It's just masked for security.\n\nSo the token is there. The 401 error was almost certainly because you weren't exporting it before running `openclaw` commands. Try the export now:\n\n```\nexport OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2\nopenclaw dashboard\n```\n\nThat should work."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":63829,"output":262,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64091,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775768914578}}
