{"type":"message","id":"07384cb0","parentId":"e6c37a83","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:38:25.405Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Good news — I ran it myself. The VPS is reachable and the gateway IS serving something on port 18789. I can see the HTML page.\n\nHere's what I found:\n- Port 18789 is **listening and externally accessible**\n- Both authenticated and unauthenticated requests return the **same page** — the OpenClaw Control UI login page\n- The token isn't doing anything on the HTTP level because the gateway serves the Control UI at the root URL regardless\n\n**The actual problem:** The URL you're hitting (`http://204.168.204.198:18789/`) is serving the **Control UI login page**, not the webchat. They're different things:\n- `/` → Control UI (administrative, login required)\n- Webchat → separate URL path (likely `/webchat` or similar — not exposed)\n\n**What's needed:** I need to find the webchat endpoint. Let me check what paths the gateway actually serves:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_61c4b1f8-8908-41d8-92c3-cac53fc940bd","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 5 http://204.168.204.198:18789/webchat 2>&1 | head -5; echo \"---\"; curl -s --max-time 5 http://204.168.204.198:18789/chat 2>&1 | head -5; echo \"---\"; curl -s --max-time 5 http://204.168.204.198:18789/api 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":15}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":73042,"output":688,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73730,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775770705397}}
