{"type":"message","id":"0aa92788","parentId":"3b62006f","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:55:07.141Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] It's working. Here's what I found and fixed:\n\n**What was wrong:**\nCaddy was configured to reverse-proxy to the gateway but had no TLS certificate. Every HTTPS connection failed because there was no cert to present. The browser got nothing usable.\n\n**What I did:**\n1. Generated a self-signed SSL certificate for `204.168.204.198`\n2. Updated Caddy's config to use the cert\n3. Caddy is now running and serving HTTPS on port 443\n\n**Try this in your browser now:**\n```\nhttps://204.168.204.198/\n```\n\nThe browser will show a security warning the first time — click through it. The gateway Control UI should load.\n\n**The token to use:** `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2`\n\n**Notes saved** to `docs/dusk-https-setup.md` — everything documented including how to restart Caddy if it stops.\n\nLet me know if it loads."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":82555,"output":219,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775771707124}}
