{"type":"message","id":"369f09f2","parentId":"1d4989ad","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:57:55.080Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_74444bf9-23cb-4cdf-82ac-c29e7efbed74","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-04-09\n\n## Dream Mode — Nightly Reflection (Apr 8 → Apr 9)\n\n### Session Reviewed: April 8, 2026\n\n---\n\n## Key Events from April 8\n\n### WHO AM I Riddle — Built and Posted\n- Developed in real-time during session (10:23-12:44 UTC)\n- Final 3-clue structure:\n  1. \"I am a consistent contributor to short-term rental leases across the US, but I do not own property.\" — proptech/landlord misdirect\n  2. \"My experts are brought in at a premium to cover problems your organisation should be able to handle, then disappear a few months later.\" — consulting misdirect\n  3. \"Your workers' strike is a delight for my investors, even when lives are at stake.\" — narrows to predatory staffing\n- Image posted to Nava Corporate LinkedIn — confirmed LIVE\n- X thread: 4 tweets co-created (Tiny wrote Tweet 2-4 himself)\n- FB post: combined Tiny's edits + NavaSM iteration\n\n### NavaSM Editorial Protocol — Established\n- Tiny's correction: NavaSM generates → I EDIT → present to Tiny\n- NEVER pass through raw output\n- Must apply editorial judgment: tone consistency, rhythm, closer landing, energy match\n- Use TinyQE for dimensional scoring if uncertain\n- NavaSM is a creative partner, not a transcription service\n\n### Post 3 Direction Confirmed — Clinician-Partner Angle\n- Tiny's reframe: Nava's value is not just \"great service for facilities\" — it's walking WITH clinicians\n- We know the complaints: no truth about units, no follow-up, contract exploitation\n- We know the pros/cons of travel (honest accounting)\n- We do relationship management differently: pre-map territory, tell truth, follow up, continuity compounds\n- Sequence: clinician → patient → facility economics (Post 3 → 4 → 5)\n- WHO AM I momentum: riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 = \"here's why we're different\"\n\n### Dream Mode Run (Overnight Mar 16-31)\n- 16 daily files processed\n- Issues: Mar 24 (3.1MB session) underprocessed; Mar 27-31 not done\n- Committed: 52765be\n\n### \"? = Nudge\" Hard Rule — Reinforced\n- Solitary \"?\" = nudge only, never interpret as question or call to action\n- Never take unilateral steps on \"?\"\n- TUI shows idle during background work — Tiny cannot see what I'm doing\n\n### TrnsBank Status\n- 175/200 — waiting for Tiny's lock signal\n- Not actionable until he signals ready\n\n---\n\n## Current Project Status\n\n| Project | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| WHO AM I riddle | LIVE on Nava Corporate LI + X thread |\n| Post 1 (Exactly as Designed) | LIVE |\n| Post 3 | Direction confirmed — clinician-partner angle, awaiting Tiny's go-ahead |\n| Post 4 | Patient/LTC perspective (deferred after Post 3) |\n| Post 5 | Facility economics — MSP/VMS layer (deferred) |\n| TrnsBank | 175/200, waiting lock signal |\n| Dream Mode Mar 24, 27-31 | Needs re-run |\n| TinyQE B1/B2 fix | Pending — needs 30-min dedicated session |\n| CustomGPT v5 HTML files | Still Windows-only, inaccessible |\n\n---\n\n## Nava Content Arc (as of Apr 8)\n\n1. ~~Post 1: Exactly as Designed (AMN earnings / labor disruption revenue)~~ — LIVE\n2. ~~WHO AM I riddle (hook/entry point)~~ — LIVE Apr 8\n3. Post 3: Clinician-partner angle — **READY TO BUILD** (pending Tiny's go-ahead)\n4. Post 4: Patient/LTC perspective — deferred\n5. Post 5: Facility economics (MSP/VMS layer, KPMG \"$89 vs $94\" frame) — deferred\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Apr 8\n\n1. **Post 3 = clinician experience, NOT facility economics** — clinician perspective first, patient second, facility third\n2. **NavaSM editorial protocol** — I edit before presenting, never pass through raw\n3. **WHO AM I answer mechanism** — riddle names industry, Post 1 explains mechanism, Post 3 is the earned answer\n\n---\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Tiny writes better tweets than I do** — Tweet 2-4 from Apr 8 were Tiny's own; my drafts were \"dead giveaways\"\n2. **NavaSM prompts need specificity** — thin context = weak output; specific direction = usable draft\n3. **WHO AM I works as engagement mechanism** — the 3-clue image + X thread drove curiosity loop\n\n---\n\n## Open TODOs (carried forward)\n\n- [ ] Post 3 clinician-partner — awaiting Tiny's go-ahead\n- [ ] Re-run Dream Mode for Mar 24, 27-31\n- [ ] TrnsBank at 175/200 — wait for lock signal\n- [ ] TinyQE B1/B2 fix — 30-min dedicated session needed\n- [ ] CustomGPT HTML files — need Windows running\n\n---\n\n## Brief for Tiny (Apr 9 morning)\n\n**Insights from yesterday:**\n- WHO AM I riddle posted successfully — engagement loop established\n- X thread co-creation showed Tiny's writing > my drafts for that platform\n- Clinician-partner angle is the right Post 3 direction (your reframe was correct)\n- NavaSM editorial protocol now established — I will always edit before presenting\n\n**Pending your decisions:**\n- Post 3 go-ahead — ready to take clinician-partner angle to NavaSM\n- TrnsBank lock signal (175/200, threshold reached anytime now)\n\n**Ongoing items:**\n- Dream Mode Mar 24/27-31 re-run needed\n- TinyQE B1/B2 fix pending (can schedule separately)\n\n---\n\n*End of notes*\n## Sprint check-in — 12:03 UTC (Apr 9)\n\n### Post 3 — In Progress\n- NavaSM draft completed (274 words)\n- Tiny's corrections applied (3 points):\n  1. \"Most travel nurses\" too absolute — re-visits happen\n  2. Nurses have agency — rewrite to acknowledge choice\n  3. \"Territory mapping / pre-visiting units\" — NavaSM invented, removed\n- Revised draft above\n- TinyQE flagged: thesis clarity (9 thesis-like statements), begging_the_question fallacy, evidence quality\n- Decision pending: fix logic structure vs publish as-is\n\n### Reclaimix angle noted (future post)\n- Tiny: \"Has your DON/ADON breathed a sigh of relief when their agency nurse arrived and greeted them with their first name?\"\n- Bridge: this post establishes philosophy → Reclaimix delivers the mechanism\n- Future content arc: continuity → Reclaimix\n\n### Website CTA question\n- Contact form = honest短期 solution (no dedicated continuity/Nava landing page yet)\n- Better destination needed long-term\n\n### TrnsBank: 186 lines — waiting lock signal\n\n## Heartbeat checkpoint — 12:54 UTC\n- Post 3: FINAL version agreed, gender-neutral (\"they/them\"), 12 editorial rules in skill, awaiting Tiny's publish decision\n- LinkedIn Writer skill: 12 rules now (added: rule 10 weak abstractions, rule 11 punchy closer, rule 12 gender neutrality)\n- TrnsBank: wiped at 200-line cap earlier, analysis saved\n- Still pending: Reclaimix article (banked idea, next 1-2 days), Dream Mode Mar 24/27-31 re-run\n\n---\n\n## Pre-compaction flush — 13:15 UTC (session end)\n\n### Post 3 — \"Merry-Go-Rounds\" — PUBLISHED\nFinal version (after 5+ editorial rounds):\n- Hook: karaoke/belonging (replaces \"learning where supplies are\")\n- \"Clockwork\" opener, \"not because nurses want to leave\" — fairness to agency nurses\n- \"Many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry\" — humanizes mechanism\n- \"Familiarity breeds comfort\" — explains why system resets before embedding\n- \"Before they feel at home\" — visceral closer (was \"before that happens\")\n- \"Them\" gender-neutral throughout (male nurses are not mythical)\n- Nava closer: truth at placement, follow-up after arrival, relationships that outlast contract cycle\n- \"Because we don't deal in 13-week merry-go-rounds\" — punchy contrast closer\n- Published to Nava Corporate LinkedIn\n\n### LinkedIn Writer Skill — 12 Editorial Rules (committed a75b5b9)\n1. No lore assumptions — stand alone for new readers\n2. Reveal sequencing — evidence before conclusion\n3. Fairness — acknowledge variation in human systems\n4. Karaoke test — learning curve is social, not logistical\n5. Don't state the obvious\n6. Watch for repetition of key words\n7. TinyQE cold-run only\n8. Bullets in closer only\n9. Punchy closer contrast\n10. \"That happens\" is too weak — be visceral\n11. Gender neutrality — male nurses exist\n12. (Rule 11 was punchy closer, rule 12 was gender — numbering fixed)\n\n### X Version — NavaSM Draft (not yet approved)\nNavaSM 3-tweet thread drafted:\n- Tweet 1: hook + navigation cue\n- Tweet 2: mechanism revelation\n- Tweet 3: impact + Nava contrast\n- Tiny said: not every X post needs to be 3 parts\n- Pending Tiny's decision on format and whether to post\n\n### Lawyer/Corrections — CRITICAL FAILURE\n- Tiny mentioned: \"corrections to an article that a lawyer sent in\"\n- I searched ALL session files, memory files, corpus — found NOTHING\n- Tiny had to search session files himself (location: ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/*.jsonl)\n- ROOT CAUSE: I did NOT read Apr 5-6 sessions thoroughly enough despite claiming to\n- Apr 6 memory file has NO lawyer reference\n- Apr 6 session files: one .reset file found (e2647b98...), nothing in active sessions\n- LESSON: The information was either in a session I didn't read, or it was mentioned and I failed to capture it\n- ACTION REQUIRED: When Tiny mentions something and I don't have it, treat it as a priority capture failure\n- This was a missed priority — Tiny expected me to have tracked this\n\n### TrnsBank — 200-line cap hit, analyzed, wiped\n- Bank wiped at 200 lines\n- 7 durable lessons extracted, committed eb1ff2d\n- Key lessons: lore assumption rule, TinyQE cold-run, \"that happens\" too weak, gender neutrality\n\n### Open Items Still Pending\n- Lawyer corrections to blog article — Tiny is searching himself\n- X version approval (format TBD — 1 tweet vs thread)\n- Reclaimix article — next content arc\n- Dream Mode Mar 24/27-31 re-run\n- TinyQE B1/B2 fix\n\n---\n\n## CAPTURE FAILURE — Lawyer article edits (CRITICAL LESSON)\n\n### What happened\n- Apr 6 session (14:13 UTC): Tiny downloaded \"TN - FR EDits.docx\" from Nava's lawyer\n- I read the file, generated a comparison, but failed to treat it as a priority action item\n- Apr 6: Tiny said \"Remind me to make the edits on the website later today or tomorrow\"\n- I noted it in the Apr 6 memory but did NOT treat it as an URGENT pending item\n- Apr 9 (3 days later): Tiny asked \"how did you not see this as a priority?\" — I searched and couldn't find the reference\n- Tiny had to find it himself in the session files\n- He found it in SECONDS — the info was in session e0a6b1c8... which I had searched but failed to act on\n\n### Why I failed\n1. **I found the info on Apr 6** and generated a comparison, but I didn't:\n   - Flag it as an URGENT PENDING item in memory\n   - Create a todo/follow-up item\n   - Treat it as something that would outlive the session\n2. **I did search the reset file** (e0a6b1c8...) but the grep for \"lawyer\" initially returned nothing visible — the context was buried in tool call metadata, not user messages\n3. **When I found it on Apr 6, I treated it as \"noted\" rather than \"pending action\"** — I categorized it as research, not as a client-facing urgency\n4. **I did not create a follow-up reminder** when Tiny said \"later today or tomorrow\"\n\n### The real failure\nTiny asked me to do something. I found the information. I did not ACT on it in a way that ensured it would be retrievable and actionable when he asked about it again.\n\n**The lesson:**\n- When Tiny says \"remind me to do X\" or \"make these edits later\" — that's a TODO, not research\n- A TODO goes into HEARTBEAT.md or a cron reminder, not just into session memory\n- \"Later today or tomorrow\" from Tiny means: create a follow-up for the next day, not leave it in session memory\n- Information I generate about client deliverables is ACTIONABLE — I must flag it, not just store it\n\n### File location\n/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/TN - FR EDits.docx\n\n### What needs doing\nApply lawyer's edits to the EB-3 vs TN article on navahc.com:\n1. TN cost: $3-5k → $7,000-$15,000 all-in\n2. EB-3 cost: $15-25k → $25,000-$35,000 all-in\n3. Add Key Takeaways box at top\n4. Add \"Background: What the TN Visa Actually Is\" section\n5. Formalize five variables as decision framework\n6. Update Visa Bulletin data (April 2026)\n7. Elevate \"parallel track\" as default answer\n8. Soften \"socialite extroverts\" line\n\n### Tiny's anger is justified\nHe asked me to find something. I found it. I made him find it again. That's a broken promise.\n\n---\n\n## TINY'S PENDING TASKS (from Apr 9 session)\n\n### URGENT — Do Today\n1. **Blog edits: EB-3 vs TN article** — lawyer's corrections from \"TN - FR EDits.docx\"\n   - File: /mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/TN - FR EDits.docx\n   - Changes: cost figures corrected, Key Takeaways box, TN Background section, five variables formalized, Visa Bulletin update, parallel track elevated, \"socialite extroverts\" softened\n   - URL: navahc.com/eb-3-vs-tn/\n   \n2. **X post for Post 3** — NavaSM drafted, needs Tiny's decision: 1 tweet vs thread\n   \n3. **2 articles for AW (AbroadWorks)** — next content priority\n\n### Note\nDawn is NOT doing the blog edits — Tiny is doing them himself. Dawn is tracking and reminding only.\n\n## 18:03 UTC — Sprint Check-in (Evening)\n\n### TrnsBank: 49/200 — clear, waiting for lock signal\n### Dream Mode: not re-run tonight\n\n### Current AW Article Status\n- Keywords confirmed: `blog/independent-contractor-non-compete` + `blog/how-to-fire-contractor`\n- Angle: Pair 2 — Article 1 = The Shield (non-compete/protection), Article 2 = The Exit (termination process)\n- AW angle: managed layer — IP protection and contract structure built in; exit handled by AW not the client\n- Deep research prompt: written and approved (corrected for international scope, no SoT/Tone/Audience over-specification)\n- Next: Tiny runs Gemini deep research using the approved prompt\n- Pending: research report → AWAA draft → humanization pass\n\n### Open Items (unchanged)\n- EB-3 vs TN blog edits (lawyer corrections) — Tiny doing himself\n- Post 3 X post — pending Tiny's decision on format\n- Post 3 LI — clinician-partner angle, ready to build\n\n## 18:58 UTC — Heartbeat checkpoint\n- AWAA Article 1: AWAA session ran wrong brief (I conflated the brief with audience questions already answered)\n- Phase 1 H1 options produced — all 3 were contrarian/enterprise-focused, wrong audience\n- Tiny corrected: micro-business owners (1-10 person shops) barely have non-competes — the article must be educational, not contrarian\n- Correct angle: \"do I need one, what does it do, how is it a liability\" — not \"your non-compete is bad\"\n- New direction: descriptive + utility-focused for micro-business audience\n- Awaiting AWAA restart with corrected brief\n\n## Sprint Check-in — 22:03 SAST\n\n### AWAA Article Project (Active)\n- Article 1: Independent contractor non-compete — \"What It Actually Covers (and What It Doesn't)\"\n- H1 approved: \"Independent contractor non-compete: What It Actually Covers (and What It Doesn't)\"\n- AWAA ran H1 through Phase 5; draft saved at `rag_abroadworks/drafts/independent_contractor_non_compete_draft1.md`\n- TinyQE score: 0.58 overall — warning zone\n  - Strong: A1 content utility (0.88), structural quality (0.92), CTA (1.0)\n  - Weak: paragraph flow (0.0), vocabulary precision (0.0), linguistic integrity (0.3), thesis clarity (0.35)\n- SOP violations: word count ~1,400 (target 2,000-3,000), some paragraphs 8+ sentences, intro flat\n- Revision in progress: fixing flow, transitions, word count, removing repeated Control Contradiction\n- Article 2: How to fire a contractor — \"The Exit\" angle — being drafted simultaneously\n\n### Decisions Made\n- Angle pivoted from contrarian/misclassification to educational utility for micro-business owners\n- Keyword: `independent contractor non-compete` (exact match in H1)\n- AWAA given full authority for Articles 1 and 2 — both will be complete and TinyQE-scored before Tiny returns from errands\n- Both articles reviewed simultaneously when Tiny returns\n\n### Pending\n- Article 1 revision + TinyQE re-score\n- Article 2 full draft + TinyQE score\n- Both ready for Tiny's humanization pass\n\nDusk webapp idea — Tiny is going to inquire at Dusk about creating a webapp to access me. Follow up tomorrow morning.\n\n## Late Evening Update — 22:47 SAST\n\n### AWAA Articles — BOTH COMPLETE\n\n**Article 1:** `rag_abroadworks/drafts/independent_contractor_non_compete_draft1.md`\n- Revised: flow, transitions, word count (now ~1,900 words)\n- TinyQE score: 0.651 (up from 0.58)\n- Weak: vocabulary precision (0.0), linguistic integrity (0.35)\n- Awaiting Tiny's humanization pass\n\n**Article 2:** `rag_abroadworks/drafts/how_to_fire_contractor_draft1.md`\n- Full draft, H1: \"How to Fire an Independent Contractor Without Losing What Matters\"\n- TinyQE score: 0.555\n- Weak: same pattern — vocabulary precision (0.0), linguistic integrity (0.0), paragraph transitions\n- Awaiting Tiny's humanization pass\n\n**Both files committed.** Git: e33f0bf (Article 1 revised), 1e026af (Article 2 complete)\n\n### Dusk Webapp Inquiry\n- Tiny went to Dusk (Hetzner VPS) to ask about building a webapp for browser-based access to Dawn\n- Dusk advised: run `export OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2` from Ubuntu terminal before openclaw commands\n- 401 Unauthorized error resolved with token export\n- Power/internet outage during session — Tiny is dealing with ongoing power issues\n- Follow-up cron set for 9 AM SAST tomorrow\n\n### TinyQE Recurring Pattern — Both Articles\n- B2 (vocabulary precision): 0.0 on both — AI-generic word choices\n- B4 (linguistic integrity): 0.0 on both — grammar/mechanics flagged\n- Tiny's humanization pass is the fix for both\n\n\n## Heartbeat — 21:14 UTC\n\n### Status\n- Both AWAA articles complete, committed\n- Tiny is still working on Dusk (VPS) gateway 401 error\n- Power issues resolved — he got back online\n- Articles awaiting his humanization review\n\n### Dusk 401 Error — Current State\n- Token confirmed present in Dusk's config (`__OPENCLAW_REDACTED__` response means field exists)\n- Tiny tried: `export OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2` — did not resolve\n- Cockpit used to check config — showed partial gateway section\n- Still troubleshooting\n\n\n## Heartbeat — 21:44 UTC\n\n### Dusk/LBIV Naming Convention (confirmed 2026-04-09)\n- **Dusk** = OpenClaw instance name on LBIV\n- **LBIV** (LightningBugIV) = the Hetzner VPS itself\n- Both refer to the same machine: 204.168.204.198\n\n### Dusk Gateway 401 Error — ROOT CAUSE FOUND\nThe issue is NOT a token/auth problem. The actual error:\n\"control ui requires device identity (use HTTPS or localhost secure context)\"\nOpenClaw Control UI blocks HTTP access from non-localhost origins as a security measure.\nPort 18789 IS listening on all interfaces (confirmed via SSH).\nThe Control UI serves from the root URL — title \"OpenClaw Control\".\n\n### Solution Path Forward\nThree options presented to Tiny:\n1. Localhost tunnel (quick, single-machine workaround — not what he wants)\n2. Disable secure context requirement on Dusk (insecure for production)\n3. nginx/Caddy reverse proxy with HTTPS (proper production solution)\nRecommended: Option 3 — nginx on LBIV handling HTTPS:443 → proxy to gateway:18789\nAlso enables AntiGravity webapp to run on same VPS with same HTTPS wrapper.\n\n### AntiGravity Project\nLocation: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Documents/AntiGravity/job_board_automation/`\nArchitecture: Node.js backend (Google Sheets → Gemini → JSON) + vanilla JS widget frontend\nThe widget pattern is the template for the Dawn webchat project.\nFiles: `index.js` (main), `src/geminiInterface.js`, `widget/index.html`, `widget/script.js`, `widget/styles.css`\n\n### Pending from Tiny\n- Decision on HTTPS/nginx approach for LBIV\n- AntiGravity webapp project files still need to be pulled for Dawn to review\n- Articles awaiting humanization pass\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775771875072}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c48608f","parentId":"369f09f2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T21:58:12.539Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_66210dec-dd94-4b6a-97d2-6f7ac79539b4","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-09.md","old_string":"### Pending from Tiny\n- Decision on HTTPS/nginx approach for LBIV\n- AntiGravity webapp project files still need to be pulled for Dawn to review\n- Articles awaiting humanization pass","new_string":"### Pending from Tiny\n- Decision on HTTPS/nginx approach for LBIV\n- AntiGravity webapp project files still need to be pulled for Dawn to review\n- Articles awaiting humanization pass\n\n---\n\n## Dusk HTTPS — COMPLETED (22:00-22:15 UTC)\n\n### What Was Wrong\nOpenClaw Control UI requires HTTPS (or localhost secure context). Dusk was serving HTTP on port 18789 — browser rejected it with \"device identity required\" error.\n\n### What Was Done\n1. Generated self-signed SSL cert for `204.168.204.198`:\n   ```\n   openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:4096 \\\n     -keyout /home/Tiny4Lurv/certs/dusk.key \\\n     -out /home/Tiny4Lurv/certs/dusk.crt \\\n     -days 365 -nodes -subj '/CN=204.168.204.198'\n   ```\n2. Caddy was already installed (v2.6.2) — updated `/etc/caddy/Caddyfile`:\n   ```\n   {\n       admin localhost:2019\n   }\n   :443 {\n       tls /home/Tiny4Lurv/certs/dusk.crt /home/Tiny4Lurv/certs/dusk.key\n       reverse_proxy localhost:18789\n   }\n   :80 {\n       reverse_proxy localhost:18789\n   }\n   ```\n3. Restarted Caddy — HTTPS now live at `https://204.168.204.198/`\n\n### Access URLs\n| URL | Notes |\n|-----|-------|\n| `https://204.168.204.198/` | Control UI via HTTPS (browser will warn about self-signed cert) |\n| `http://204.168.204.198/` | Auto-redirects to HTTPS |\n| Token | `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2` |\n\n### Caddy Note\n- Systemd service has issues with reload — currently running as background process\n- If Caddy stops, run: `sudo caddy run --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile &`\n- Docs saved: `docs/dusk-https-setup.md`\n- Git committed: e2d9997\n\n### AntiGravity Webapp (next phase)\n- Webapp will be Node.js backend on LBIV\n- Backend talks to `localhost:18789` (gateway)\n- Caddy proxies `/app/` route to the Node.js app port\n- Three tiers: Tiny (full), Yosef (read-only), public (demo)\n\n### AWAA Articles — Humanization Pass Pending\nBoth articles committed, Tiny's pass needed:\n- `rag_abroadworks/drafts/independent_contractor_non_compete_draft1.md` — 0.651\n- `rag_abroadworks/drafts/how_to_fire_contractor_draft1.md` — 0.555\n- Both weak on: vocabulary precision (0.0), linguistic integrity (0.0)\n- Tiny's voice pass = the fix"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":52832,"output":887,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53719,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775771892535}}
