{"type":"message","id":"48642edf","parentId":"1b3aafe1","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:01:12.222Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Yes — that pending request is from your Windows machine. It's your browser trying to log in to the Control UI. `Win32` + `openclaw-control-ui` = the browser on your PC hitting `https://204.168.204.198/`.\n\nThe one that's already paired (`linux` + `cli`) — that's me. I'm connected from my Linux/WSL session.\n\nGo ahead and approve it."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":58281,"output":176,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58457,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775772072215}}
{"type":"message","id":"c98ff9b7","parentId":"48642edf","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:02:00.294Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-04-10 00:01 GMT+2] You see, that's a problem, because what if you are offline and I don't have my laptop. How am I to approve pairing then?"}],"timestamp":1775772120236}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f3d2981","parentId":"c98ff9b7","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:02:17.105Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] That's a real concern. Here's the honest breakdown:\n\n**Why you're seeing \"pairing required\":**\nThe Control UI on Dusk has device pairing enforced — it's an extra security layer on top of the token. Without an approved device, even with the correct token, you can't log in through the browser.\n\n**The problem you're describing:**\nIf I'm offline and you don't have a pre-approved device, you literally cannot approve a new device. The pairing flow requires CLI access to run `openclaw devices approve`. No CLI = no approval = no access. That's a lockout scenario.\n\n**Solutions:**\n\n**1. Pre-approve everything now (best for your situation)**\nApprove every device you own — laptop, phone, tablet, work PC — right now while we're connected. Then you're never hitting the pairing screen. To add a new device later, you'd need CLI access (phone with SSH app, or ask me when I'm online).\n\n**2. Use the gateway token directly (API access only)**\nThe OpenClaw API itself doesn't require device pairing — just the token. You could access it via curl or a tool that supports bearer token auth, without needing the Control UI. More manual, but works from any device.\n\n**3. Disable pairing requirement for webchat**\nChange Dusk's gateway config so webchat doesn't require device pairing — only token. Less secure, but accessible from anywhere with just the token. I can do this now if you want the tradeoff.\n\n**My take:**\nPre-approve all your devices now. It's the right balance — you stay in control, no lockout, and if a new device needs access in future you have options (CLI, ask me, or I pre-approve it in a session while you're traveling).\n\nWant me to show you how to pre-approve everything in one shot?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":58503,"output":775,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59278,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775772137096}}
