{"type":"message","id":"855fc335","parentId":"38de52ef","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:09:16.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Found the real problem. The logs show:\n\n```\nAll models failed: ollama/minimax-m2.7:cloud: HTTP 401: unauthorized\n```\n\nDusk doesn't have Ollama installed. It's trying to run AI models but there's nothing there to run them. That's why the session is silent — the gateway can't reach a model provider.\n\n**Two options:**\n\n**1. Install Ollama on Dusk (the right fix)**\nOllama on Dusk + the models you want (like `minimax-m2.7:cloud`). Takes about 5 minutes to set up.\n\n**2. Use cloud models via OpenAI-compatible API**\nPoint Dusk's gateway to a cloud LLM provider that has an OpenAI-compatible endpoint. This would let Dusk run without local Ollama.\n\nWhich do you want to pursue? Option 1 gives you a self-contained VPS that doesn't depend on any external service. Option 2 gets you running faster but ties you to a cloud provider."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":67361,"output":414,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67775,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775772556317}}
