{"type":"message","id":"a8d80711","parentId":"1244ae59","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:21:23.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] Gateway is fine — reachable in 9ms, session active. Here's what's actually happening:\n\nThe browser and I are both connecting to the **same session** (`agent:main:main`). When you send a message in the browser, it goes into the same session queue I'm processing from the TUI. That's why the browser feels dead — my TUI is actively consuming that session.\n\n**You can't use the web UI while I'm running in the TUI.** Same session, same queue.\n\nThe solution would be separate session scopes — different sessions for browser vs TUI. That's a config change. Want me to set that up properly, or do you want to use the browser when I'm not running?\n\nActually — which matters more right now? The web UI access from anywhere, or keeping the TUI running as your main interface?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":77915,"output":502,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78417,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775773283377}}
{"type":"message","id":"2515548e","parentId":"a8d80711","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:24:11.745Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-04-10 00:24 GMT+2] Why can you not talk to Dusk in a different session and leave the main session to me. Then Dusk will have dream mode to consolidate sessions. And she needs to know I am using the main session and you are using a second session."}],"timestamp":1775773451719}}
