{"type":"message","id":"6c9523ea","parentId":"a303ee88","timestamp":"2026-04-09T23:22:05.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] The issue is structural — there's only one session (`agent:main:main`) and both the TUI and browser are hitting it. When I'm in TUI, I'm consuming that session's queue. Browser has nothing to show because the session is being processed by me.\n\nThe fix requires a second agent bound to the browser. Let me set that up:\n\n```\nopenclaw agents add dusk-browser --workspace /home/Tiny4Lurv/.openclaw/agents/dusk-browser\n```\n\nThen bind it to the webchat channel so Tiny's browser goes to a separate session while I'm on TUI with `main`. Want me to proceed?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":56807,"output":478,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57285,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775776925042}}
