{"type":"message","id":"947b7721","parentId":"a336dfd5","timestamp":"2026-04-10T00:04:46.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update the git repo section and add a note about the Dusk agent setup that's still pending:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_124a2d2e-21fa-47ff-b024-7f7ae0b6907b","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"## Git Repository\n\n```bash\n# Clone the Dawn workspace git repo\ngit clone https://github.com/tiny4lurv/dawn-workspace.git ~/.openclaw/workspace\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit log -1 --format=\"%H %s\"  # last commit\n```\n\nLast recorded commit: see `GIT_REPO.md` in this folder.\n\n---\n\n## Dusk VPS Agent (Pending Setup — Do This After Restoring)\n\nThe restore kit sets up your local machine. Dusk (the remote VPS) needs its OWN agent configured separately.\n\nOn Dusk, as Tiny4Lurv:\n```bash\nopenclaw agents add dusk --workspace /home/Tiny4Lurv/.openclaw/agents/dusk\nopenclaw agents bind dusk --channel webchat\n```\n\nThis creates a SEPARATE AI peer you can reach when Dawn is offline and your laptop is unavailable. She is not a subagent — she is a peer with her own identity, workspace, and session space.\n\n> This step is PENDING if you're reading this from a fresh restore. Run it on Dusk after the restore is complete.\n\n---\n\n## Common Issues","oldText":"## Git Repository\n\n```bash\n# Clone the Dawn workspace git repo\ngit clone https://github.com/tiny4lurv/dawn-workspace.git ~/.openclaw/workspace\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit log -1 --format=\"%H %s\"  # last commit\n```\n\nLast recorded commit: see `GIT_REPO.md` in this folder.\n\n---\n\n## Common Issues","path":"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Apps/Dawn-Restore/RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":56626,"output":727,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57353,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":17